			  <section id="1.3.2 Brief System Description" level="4">
				  <title>1.3.2 Brief System Description</title>
				  <content>
					  <para>
						  See Fig. 1.2 for System Configuration
						  of NTDS
					  </para>
					  <para>
						  The main units that
						  constitute the NTDS consist of an EDL,               FVA, LCU, RCU,
						  Console, Processing Cabinet and a Winch with fairlead.
					  </para>
					  <para>
						  <figure>
							  <graphic
							  fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/fig_1_2.gif"
></graphic>
							  <figtitle>Fig. 1.2: System Configuration of NTDS</figtitle>
						  </figure>
					  </para>
					  <para>
						  The
						  Winch helps in detecting the incoming torpedoes               by means
						  of deploying FOTC over the ship’s stern side through a Fairlead
						  while the EDL is designed to launch EADs using compressed
						  air from               corresponding FVA.
					  </para>
					  <para>
						  Each EDL accommodates 10 FVAs/Device
						  launch barrels which are Line Replaceable Units (LRUs)
						  that can be               removed or installed with standard tools.
						  Each barrel assembly has               a length of approximately 1m
						  and diameter of 0.175m with a weight               of 13kg. The EDL
						  has a provision to detect EIGHT types of EADs (stores)
						  loaded by means of its contacts at the contact plug assembly. This
						  information (“store present” and “store type”) is available
						  at the               Consoles. The EDL can be locally (LCU) or remotely
						  (RCU) controlled               for launching the EAD. Each EAD is
						  independently controllable. The               EDL transmits its status
						  to the processing units through standard               RS485 link.
						  A Console provides visual display of the target parameters
						  and communicates with the processing cabinet through standard
						  RS485               link. All the NTDS sub-systems are communicated
						  with processing cabinet               by electrical or optical communication.
						  The EDL operates on 115V,               50/60Hz, 1 Phase ship’s supply
						  or 3 Phase 380, 415, 450VAC. A Sounder               mounted within
						  the body of the EDL is used to generate a two-tone               alarm
						  when the launcher is put to Remote Mode.
					  </para>
					  <para>
						  <h6>
							  Main
							  Units of the NTDS
						  </h6>
					  </para>
					  <para>
						  <table frame="box" rules="all">
