					  <section id="1.3.2.3.8 Fairlead" level="6">
						  <title>1.3.2.3.8 Fairlead</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  The pictorial view of Fairlead is
								  shown in Fig. 1.11.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  The fairlead is mounted over the stern of the ship through
								  which the towed component (cable) is deployed. A water
								  shower, with                   a total of three nozzles (on top side
								  of the inner surface of the                   fairlead) is fitted
								  in the fairlead. The water shower is directed                   over
								  the cable to remove any debris, mud etc whilst recovering the
								  tow cable. Each nozzle can discharge 0.355 ltr/sec.
								  The amount of                   water that is required for washing
								  whole tow cable while recovering                   is 1000 litres
								  (approx.).
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <figure>
									  <graphic
									  fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/fig_1_11.gif"
></graphic>
