				  <section id="1.3.2.4 Console" level="5">
					  <title>1.3.2.4 Console</title>
					  <content>
						  <para>
							  A pictorial view of the console is shown
							  in Fig. 1.12.
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  The console
							  provides the man-machine interface and displays                 all
							  information. Processed data from the towed sub-system is made
							  available to the System Operator and OOW in visual and
							  audible form                 on the console. With the assistance of
							  the System Operator the system                 can propose defensive
							  actions to be taken by the ship in the face                 of the
							  detected threat. Such defensive actions may be composed of
							  passive countermeasures or a range of active countermeasures.
							  Input                 supply to this unit is 115 VAC, 50/60Hz, 1Ø
							  or 380VAC/415VAC/450VAC                 50Hz/60Hz,3∅, comes from the
							  ships mains. The console interfaces with                 the Winch
							  through an RS-485 link. It is also interfaced with the Cabinet
							  for communication.
						  </para>
