        <section id="1.3.3 Self-Test" level="4">
          <title>1.3.3 Self-Test</title>
          <content>
            <para>
              Each Sub-system of NTDS
              is capable of self-test and               transfer status when Processing
              Cabinet sends query to that particular               sub-system. When
              Sub systems are switched ON, health monitoring is               initiated
              by a Built in Test Equipment (BITE) and fault diagnosis
              is conducted upto the LRU level. The results of the self-test
              for               EDL are made available at the LCU by means of flashing
              LEDs. The same               BITE data is also sent to the Cabinet/RCU
              via RS-485.
            </para>
          </content>
        </section>
        <section id="1.3.4 Modes of operation for EDL" level="4">
          <title>1.3.4 Modes of operation for EDL</title>
          <content>
            <para>
              The Expendable Acoustic
              Devices loaded in the EDL (Port/Stbd)               can be launched
              in 3 modes.
            </para>
            <para>
              <ol type="1">
                <li>Local mode</li>
                <li>Remote mode</li>
                <li>Auto mode</li>
              </ol>
            </para>
          </content>
          <section id="1.3.4.1 Local mode" level="5">
            <title>1.3.4.1 Local mode</title>
            <content>
              <para>
                When the operator initiates this mode, the EDL can be operated from the LCU, the EADs can be fired from the LCU. Load the EAD on the Barrel and carry out the following procedure:
              </para>
              <para>(a) When power is available to the launcher, the `POWER AVL` indicator  (White) on the LCU glows.</para>
              <para>(b) Switch the 2 position `Power ON/OFF` switch to `ON`. `Power ON` indicator (White) on the LCU glows.</para>
              <para>(c) The 2 way key switch, SAFE/ENABLE is by default in SAFE position.</para>
              <para>(d) The 3-way Key switch, `REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM` is by default in SAFE position.</para>
              <para>(e) Set the 2-way key switch, `SAFE/ENABLE`, to ENABLE.</para>
              <para>(f) While firing switch the 3-way key switch momentarily to LOCAL ARM  with one hand and press the firing button simultaneously with the other hand.</para>
              <para>(g) Sounder will come on when 3-way key switch is put to LOCAL ARM.</para>
              <para>
                (h) Inputs to the LCU are:
                <para>
                  <ol type="i">
                    <li>Position of 5-way mechanical selector switch on each FVA (SAFE, VENT and ARM proximity sensors).</li>
                    <li>State of Reservoir pressure (Pressure sensor)</li>
                    <li>EAD present indication. </li>
                  </ol>
                </para>
              </para>
              <para>
                (i) Output from the LCU are the following: <para>
                  <ol type="i">
                    <li>Firing signal to the solenoid valve.</li>
                    <li>Status of the launcher to RCU and Cabinet.</li>

                  </ol>
                </para>
              </para>

              <para>The flowchart corresponding to the operation of EDL in Local mode along with its procedure is given in the figure below:</para>
              <para>
                <figure>
                  <graphic fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/EDL_Local_Mode.gif"></graphic>
                  <figtitle>EDL Operation-Local Mode</figtitle>
                </figure>
              </para>
            </content>
          </section>
          <section id="1.3.4.2 Remote Mode" level="5">
            <title>1.3.4.2 Remote Mode</title>
            <content>
              <para>While operating the launcher from the RCU, the 3-way key  switch, REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM  is put to REMOTE. The operation of the launcher from RCU is identical to that of LCU. It may be noted that when operating the system through RCU, ensure that link between RCU &amp; LCU is established.</para>
              <para>(a) When power is available to the launcher, the `POWER AVL` indicator (White) on the LCU glows.</para>
              <para>(b) When power is available to the launcher, the `POWER AVL` indicator (White) on the RCU glows.</para>
              <para>(c) Switch the 2 position `Power ON/OFF` switch to `ON`. `Power ON` indicator (White) on the LCU glows.</para>
              <para>(d) Switch the 2 position `Power ON/OFF` switch to `ON`. `Power ON` indicator (White) on the RCU glows.</para>
              <para>(e) The 2 way key switch, SAFE/ENABLE is by default in SAFE position on LCU.</para>
              <para>(f) The 3-way Key switch, `REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM` is by default in SAFE position on LCU.</para>
              <para>(g) The 2 way key switch, AUTO/MANUAL is by default in MANUAL position on RCU.</para>
              <para>The flowchart corresponding to the operation of EDL in Remote mode along with its procedure is given in the figure below:</para>
              <para>(h) The 3-way Key switch, `AUTO ARM/SAFE/REMOTE ARM` is by default in SAFE position On RCU</para>
              <para>(i) The 2-way key switch, `SAFE/ENABLE`, to ENABLE on LCU</para>
              <para>(j) The 2-way key switch, `AUTO/MANUAL to AUTO on RCU.</para>
              <para>(k) 3 way key switch REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM to REMOTE on LCU </para>
              <para>(l) While firing switch the 3-way key  switch momentarily to REMOTE ARM  with one hand and press the firing button simultaneously with the other hand on RCU</para>
              <para>(m) Sounder will come on when 3-way key  switch is put to REMOTE ARM .</para>
              <para>(n) Inputs to the RCU: Status of launcher via RS485 communication link.</para>
              <para>
                (o) Output from the RCU are the following: <para>
                  <ol type="i">
                    <li>Firing signal to the solenoid valve</li>
                    <li>Status of RCU to Cabinet</li>

                  </ol>
                </para>
              </para>

              <para>
                <figure>
                  <graphic fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/EDL_Remote_Mode.gif"></graphic>
                  <figtitle>EDL Operation-Remote Mode</figtitle>
                </figure>
              </para>
            </content>
          </section>
          <section id="1.3.4.3 Auto Mode" level="5">
            <title>1.3.4.3 Auto Mode</title>
            <content>
              <para>The operating procedure of the launcher from the Processing Cabinet is as given below:</para>
              <para>(a) When power is available to the launcher, the `POWER AVL` indicator (White) on the LCU glows.</para>
              <para>(b) When power is available to the launcher, the `POWER AVL` indicator (White) on the RCU glows.</para>
              <para>(c) Switch the 2 position `Power ON/OFF` switch to `ON`. `Power ON` indicator (White) on the LCU glows.</para>
              <para>(d) Switch the 2 position `Power ON/OFF` switch to `ON`. `Power ON` indicator (White) on the RCU glows.</para>
              <para>(e) The 2 way key switch, SAFE/ENABLE is by default in SAFE position on LCU.</para>
              <para>(f) The 3-way Key switch, `REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM` is by default in SAFE position on LCU.</para>
              <para>(g) The 2 way key switch, AUTO/MANUAL is by default in MANUAL position on RCU.</para>
              <para>(h) The 3-way Key switch, `AUTO ARM/SAFE/REMOTE ARM` is by default in SAFE position On RCU</para>
              <para>(i) The 2-way key switch, `SAFE/ENABLE`, to ENABLE on LCU</para>
              <para>(j) The 2-way key switch, `AUTO/MANUAL to AUTO on RCU.</para>
              <para>(k) 3 way key switch REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM to REMOTE on LCU </para>
              <para>(l) The 3-way Key switch, `AUTO ARM/SAFE/REMOTE ARM` is on AUTO ARM position On RCU.</para>
              <para>
                <figure>
                  <graphic fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/EDL_Auto_Mode.gif"></graphic>
                  <figtitle>EDL Operation-Auto Mode</figtitle>
                </figure>
              </para>
            </content>
          </section>
        </section>
        <section id="1.3.5 Modes of Operation-Winch" level="4">
          <title>1.3.5 Modes of Operation-Winch</title>
          <content>
            <para>
              The winch can be operated
              locally from the Local Panel               (MCP) at the winch station
              or remotely from the Remote Panel (not               in the scope
              of supply) located in the Ops Room. Selection of Local/Remote
              operation is possible only at the Local Panel. Once Remote
              mode is               initiated the system can be returned to the
              Local mode by changing               the mode of operation (LOCAL/REMOTE)
              at the Local panel only. Similarly,               selection of Emergency
              stop, Standby and Operation modes is possible               from the
              Local Panel only.
            </para>
            <para>
              The winch can operate in the               following modes:
            </para>
            <para>
              <ol type="1">
                <li>Standby Mode</li>
                <li>Operational Mode</li>
                <li>Maintenance Mode</li>
              </ol>
            </para>
          </content>
          <section id="1.3.5.1 Standby Mode" level="5">
            <title>1.3.5.1 Standby Mode</title>
            <content>
              <para>
                In this mode, the system
                is ready for operation. Deployment                 or recovery of
                the FOTC cable is not possible. The system is in power
                saving mode and shutdowns subunits, Level Wind VFD and Drum VFD.
                In                 this mode Supply Available Indicator, Emergency
                (if switch pressed)                 indicators on the MCP top panel
                are illuminated.
              </para>
            </content>
          </section>
          <section id="1.3.5.2 Operational Mode" level="5">
            <title>1.3.5.2 Operational Mode</title>
            <content>
              <para>
                In this mode, the FOTC
                cable can be deployed till 7                 meters (3 turns) of cable
                remains on the winch drum, the motor stops                 rotating
                the winch drum and deployment of cable will stop. The operator
                can now only recover the cable. During recovery, the
                drive motor stops                 rotating the winch drum and thereby
                recovery of cable, once the FOTC                 cable length reaches
                maximum, i.e. 913 meters. In this mode Supply                 Available
                Indicator, System Ready Indicator and Emergency Indicators
                on the MCP top panel are illuminated.
              </para>

              <para>
                <note>
                  <para style="color:red">
                    Note: It is important that the length of
                    FOTC cable being deployed                     or recovered shall not
                    exceed its permissible limits, else the limit
                    switches may damage.
                  </para>
                </note>
              </para>


            </content>
          </section>
          <section id="1.3.5.3 Maintenance Mode" level="5">
            <title>1.3.5.3 Maintenance Mode</title>
            <content>
              <para>
                This mode is for carrying
                out maintenance. When this                 mode is initiated, switch
                4 and switch 5 located inside the rotary                 cam limit
                switch will be overridden and allows the FOTC to be removed
                from the drum completely. When this mode is selected, the
                SYSTEM READY                 indicator will blink continuously
              </para>
            </content>
          </section>
