              <para>
                <h6>Hardware Implementation of the LCU</h6>
              </para
  >
              <para>The LCU hardware is integrated with the following hardware:</para
  >
              <para>
                <ol type="1">
                  <li>LCU PLD Card</li>
                  <li>LCU CPU Card</li>
                  <li>Power Supply Card</li>
                </ol>
              </para>
              <para>
                The block diagram of the LCU is shown in Fig. 1.46.
                The LCU has one PLD card and one CPU card. The PLD card is used for
                fire control, controls 10 barrels. The output of the PLD card is the
                firing pulse to the solenoid valve. The CPU card is used for displaying
                the status of the EDL and for communications. Output of the card conveying
                the status of the EDL is sent to the RCU and Cabinet through an RS485
                interface cable. Launcher available/ready indications for each launcher
                are also sent from this card. The Block ‘D’ located in PLD Card is
                a driver whose output is given to the solenoid valve; the Block T
                is a monostable multi-vibrator which gives timing to the firing pulse.
                Inputs to the PLD card are received from the RCU and LCU firing buttons.
                The input power supply to these cards 24V DC, which comes from power
                supply card.
              </para>
              <para>
                <figure>
                  <graphic fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/fig_1_46.gif"></graphic>
                  <figtitle>Fig. 1.46: Block diagram of LCU</figtitle>
                </figure>
              </para>

            </content>
            <section id="1.4.1.4.1 LCU PLD Card" level="6">
              <title>1.4.1.4.1 LCU PLD Card</title>
              <content>
                <para>
                  When the 2-way lock switch is put to ENABLE mode, the
                  24V supply is made available to the 3-way lock switch. In either the
                  “LOCAL ARM” or “REMOTE ARM” modes, the 24V supply is available to
                  V1, which is given to the driver ‘D’ circuit supplying power to the
                  solenoids.
                </para>
                <para>
                  In ‘LOCAL ARM’ mode, if the ENABLE is present
                  and “FIRE” push button is pressed, the signal is generated. In “REMOTE
                  ARM” mode, if the ENABLE is present and “FIRE” input command is received
                  from the RCU, the signal is generated. This signal is shaped by the
                  monostable multivibrator, and the timed output is given to the “Driver”
                  circuit. If 24V is present on V1, the signal is generated for the
                  solenoid coils.
                </para>
                <para>
                  <h6>Functions</h6>
                </para>
                <para>
                  The functions
                  of this card are as follows:
                </para>


                <para>(a) Takes inputs from the LCU front panel (firing buttons).</para>
                <para>(b) Processes input signals and converts them into digital signals.</para>
                <para>(c) Generate firing pulse to the FVA solenoid valve</para>
                <para>(d) Takes 24V DC and converts it into 5VDC/50mA.</para>


                <para>
                  <h6>Block diagram description</h6>
                </para>
                <para>
                  See
                  Fig. 1.48 for the block diagram of the LCU PLD card.
                </para>
                <para>
                  For
                  schematic diagram of the LCU PLD card, <h6>
                    <a onclick="javascript:parent.showPDF(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/Plate_3_1.pdf&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;" actuate="user">
                      Click here.<img src="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/book.jfif" style="height:40px;width:50px;"/>
                    </a>
                  </h6>
                </para>
                <para
  >
                  It consists of Digital inputs block, Controller block, Digital outputs
                  block and Power supply block.
                </para>
                <para>
                  <figure>
                    <graphic fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/fig_1_48.gif"></graphic>
                    <figtitle>Fig. 1.48: Block diagram-LCU-PLD Card</figtitle>
                  </figure>
                </para>
                <para>
                  <h6>(a) Digital inputs block:</h6> LCU have
                  24 digital isolated inputs, which are isolated. Isolated digital inputs
                  are Local fire, Remote fire and the mode inputs. It takes 24V DC input
                  signal from the system and convert it to 5V output for PLD as input.
                </para
  >
                <para>
                  <h6>(b) Controller block:</h6> This block takes the isolated
                  input from the system and generates output as per internal logic.
                  PLD is operating on maximum 5V supply voltage. PLD is having ISP programming
                  capability.
                </para>
                <para>
                  <h6>(c) Digital outputs block: </h6>LCU has
                  11 isolated outputs. It takes 5VDC inputs from the PLD and converts
                  to 24VDC output signal for driving the solenoid Viz., isolated switching
                  circuit.
                </para>
                <para>
                  <h6>(d) Power supply block:</h6> This section
                  has DC-DC converter. It takes 24V DC/200mA and gives 5VDC/500mA output
                  to various ICs in the circuitry.
                </para>
                <para>
                  <h6>Logical description</h6
  >
                </para>
                <para>
                  LCU PLD is operating in 2 modes, Local fire and Remote
                  fire. When SAFE/ENABLE switch is set to ENABLE then LCU take action
                  on Local fire and Remote fire input signal and generate respected
                  outputs. If ENABLE signal is not present then LCU will not take any
                  action.
                </para>
                <para>
                  <h6>a) Local Fire mode:</h6> When the input signals
                  ENABLE, LOCAL ARM, LOCAL FIRE-1 inputs are given to the PLD then PLD
                  will check following condition true then PLD will make the Solenoid
                  output-1 ON for time 10 sec and then OFF. If you are in Local fire
                  mode and give any Remote fire input signal PLD will not generate outputs.
                </para
  >
                <para>
                  Solenoid 1 = Enable &amp; Local ARM &amp; Local Fire 1 &amp;
                  Timer1
                </para>
                <para>
                  In the same way, the other 9 input signals are
                  processes and generate the firing signals to the Solenoids.
                </para
  >
                <para>
                  <h6>b) Remote Fire mode:</h6> When the input signals ENABLE,
                  REMOTE, REMOTE FIRE-1 inputs are given to the PLD then PLD will check
                  following condition true then PLD will ON the Solenoid output-1 for
                  time 10 sec and then OFF. If you are in Remote fire mode and give
                  any Local fire input signal PLD will not generate outputs.
                </para>
                <para
  >Solenoid 1 = Enable &amp; Remote &amp; Remote Fire 1 &amp; Timer1</para
  >
                <para>
                  In the same way, the other 9 input signals are processes and
                  generate the firing signals to the Solenoids
                </para>
                <para>
                  <h6>
                    PLD Card
                    connector details
                  </h6>
                </para>
                <para>
                  The details of connectors located
                  at facial of this card are shown in the Table-3 below:
                </para>
                <para
  >
                  <h6>Table-3: PLD Card connector’s details</h6>
                </para>
