        <section id="1.4.2 Remote Control Unit RCU" level="4">
          <title>1.4.2 Remote Control Unit (RCU)</title>
          <content>
            <para>
              <h6>Introduction</h6>
            </para>
            <para>
              For Introduction to RCU,
              <a onclick="javascript:parent.VideoFrame(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Video/videos/V6_intro_RCU.mp4&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;" actuate="uSer">
                Click here <img src="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/video.gif" style="height:40px;width:50px;" />
              </a>
            </para>

            <para>
              The pictorial view
              of RCU is shown in Fig. 1.57
            </para>
            <para>
              The RCU is housed in a 19”
              rack. It is used to operate the EDL from a position other than from
              the launcher. The RCU can be used to operate and control EDL (PORT/STBD)
              remotely. When the LOCAL ARM/SAFE/REMOTE Key Switch located on the
              LCU (PORT/STBD) is put to the “REMOTE” position, fire commands are
              routed to the RCU and permits the operator to control independent
              EDLs. Firing from Processing Cabinet (Auto-Fire), of the EDL is possible
              via RCU . This unit can operate at 115 VAC, 50Hz/60Hz, 1∅ or 380VAC/415VAC/450VAC
              50Hz/60Hz, 3∅ with a power rating of 50 W (Approx.)
            </para>
            <para>
              <figure>
                <graphic fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/fig_1_57.gif"></graphic>
                <figtitle>Fig. 1.57: Pictorial view of RCU</figtitle>
              </figure>
            </para>
            <para>
              <h6>Functions</h6>
            </para>
            <para>
              The functions
              of RCU are given below:
            </para>
            <para>
              <ol type="a">
                <li>
                  Capable of controlling each launch barrel independently by means
                  of individual push buttons &amp; controlled keys.
                </li>
                <li>Coordinate the operation of the EDL, FVA and Processing Cabinet.</li>
                <li>
                  Receives Fire commands from Cabinet if in AUTO ARM mode and generate
                  fire commands if in REMOTE ARM mode,. It also receive EDL information.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Controlling the mode of operation for the EDL (REMOTE ARM/AUTO
                  ARM).
                </li>
                <li>
                  Indicate availability of an EAD in the barrel by means of glowing
                  lamp in blue on RCU front panel.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Indicate launcher readiness to fire by means of glowing lamp in
                  green on RCU front panel.
                </li>
                <li>
                  By two hand operations, selecting ‘REMOTE ARM’ position on ‘AUTO
                  ARM/SAFE/REMOTE ARM’ Key Switch and by pressing ‘FIRE’ push button
                  to Launch EAD.
                </li>
                <li>Receive Launcher byte data via a RS-485 serial link.</li>
                <li>Provide communication with Processing Cabinet via RS485 link.</li>
                <li>
                  Verifies the system operational lamp status by carrying out a
                  lamp-test.
                </li>
              </ol>
            </para>
            <para>
              <h6>Controls and Indicators</h6>
            </para>
            <para>
              The
              various controls &amp; indicators provided on the front panel of the
              RCU are given in the Table-6.
            </para>
            <para>
              <h6>
                Table-6: Controls &amp;
                Indicators on RCU
              </h6>
            </para>
            <para>
