                      Shows the availability of 115 VAC, 50Hz/60Hz, 1∅ or 380VAC/415VAC/450VAC
                      50Hz/60Hz, 3∅ voltage from the ship’s mains.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>2</td>
                    <td>Power ON Indicator</td>
                    <td>Illuminate white, when Power ON/OFF switch at ON position.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>3</td>
                    <td>2 Way key switch</td>
                    <td>This key switch toggles the launcher between AUTO and MANUAL modes.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>4</td>
                    <td>Power ON/OFF switch</td>
                    <td>This switch is used for switching ON power to the launcher.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>5</td>
                    <td>3 Way key switch</td>
                    <td>
                      This key switch is used to put the launcher to AUTO ARM/SAFE/REMOTE
                      ARM.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>6</td>
                    <td>Push button switches</td>
                    <td>
                      There are 20 push button switches. One set each (10 no’s) for
                      PORT and STBD launchers. These switches are used to fire the EAD.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>7</td>
                    <td>AVL Indicator</td>
                    <td>
                      <para>
                        This indicator illuminates in Blue and indicate the readiness
                        of the individual (20 no’s) EAD when the following conditions are
                        met:
                      </para>
                      <para>
                        <ol type="a">
                          <li>SAFE/ENABLE Key Switch on LCU is ENABLE Position</li>
                          <li>Power Good</li>
                          <li>Pressure Good</li>
                          <li>Firing Valve at ARM position</li>
                          <li>EAD (Store) present</li>
                          <li>REMOTE / SAFE / LOCAL ARM Key switch on LCU is in REMOTE position.</li>
                          <li>AUTO/MANUAL Key Switch on RCU is in AUTO position.</li>
                        </ol>
                      </para>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>8</td>
                    <td>RDY Indicator</td>
                    <td>
                      This indicator illuminates in Green when the switch ‘REMOTE ARM/SAFE/AUTO
                      ARM’ is set to ‘REMOTE ARM’ position and “AVL” is present for individually
                      (20 no’s) EAD.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>9</td>
                    <td>Lamp Test</td>
                    <td>
                      It is a push button switch provided for conducting a Lamp Test
                      to verify whether all the lamps on the RCU panel are working. This
                      confirms the health status of all the lamps provided.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>10</td>
                    <td>Cabinet Communication Status indicator</td>
                    <td>
                      This LED will glow white when the link between Processing Cabinet
                      and RCU is established.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>11</td>
                    <td>Fuse 1</td>
                    <td>
                      Fuse-1 (2A) protects RCU (power supply card-1) from excessive
                      current.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>12</td>
                    <td>Fuse 2</td>
                    <td>
                      Fuse-2 (2A) protects RCU (power supply card-2) from excessive
                      current.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="2">13</td>
                    <td>PORT Remote Indicator</td>
                    <td>
                      This lamp is illuminated in green to indicate the state of the
                      PORT EDL represented if EDL is in Remote.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>PORT Communication Status Indicator</td>
                    <td>
                      This LED will glow white when the Communication link between EDL
                      (PORT) and RCU is established.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="2">14</td>
                    <td>STBD Remote Indicator</td>
                    <td>
                      This lamp is illuminated in green to indicate the state of the
                      STBD EDL represented if EDL is in Remote.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>STBD Communication Status Indicator</td>
                    <td>
                      This LED will glow white when the Communication link between EDL
                      (STBD) and RCU is established.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>15</td>
                    <td>Dimmer 1 and Dimmer 2</td>
                    <td>To control the brightness of the Lamps.</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </para>
            <para>
