                        <td>12</td>
                        <td>Gear box options</td>
                        <td>H: H – Cover</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>13</td>
                        <td>Gear Box Type</td>
                        <td>In line Helical </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>14</td>
                        <td>Gear Box Ratio</td>
                        <td>5:1</td>
                      </tr>
                    </tbody>
                  </table>
                </para>
              </content>
            </section>
            <section id="1.4.3.6.2 Level Wind Proximity Sensors" level="6">
              <title>1.4.3.6.2 Level Wind Proximity Sensors</title>
              <content>
                <para>
                  The level wind assembly is equipped with two inductive
                  type proximity sensors located on the extremities of the Sliding C
                  structure. These sensors detect the position of level wind assembly
                  when it approaches within 10-20mm and activate its corresponding relay
                  so as to stop the level wind motor operation and stop further movement
                  of the assembly. The sensors have two LED indicators, one will glow
                  green when supply is ON, the other will glow yellow to indicate that
                  the limit has been reached. The specifications of level wind proximity
                  sensors are as follows:
                </para>

                <para>(a) Sensing distance: 10-20 mm</para>
                <para>(b) Wiring connection: 4 wire</para>
                <para>(c) Supply voltage: 24 VDC with reverse polarity protection.</para>
              </content>
            </section>
          </section>
          <section id="1.4.3.7 Slip Ring Assembly " level="5">
            <title>1.4.3.7 Slip Ring Assembly </title>
            <content>
              <para>See Fig. 1.74 for Slip Ring Assembly</para>

              <para>
                The Slip Ring assembly,
                mounted on the hollow shaft of the winch, is a device which connects
                the Electrical and Optical signals between the rotary and stationary
                parts of the winch (From deck cable to the Fiber Optic Tow Cable connector).
                The optical and electrical signals from the rotating part of the winch
                (Winch drum junction box containing Optical Repeater and Fiber Optic
                Tow Cable connector) are connected to the stationary junction box
                (SRJB) mounted on the starboard side of the winch support structure.
                The Slip Ring Assembly is provided on the rotational axis of the drum
                to transfer electrical and optical signals from the deck cable to
                the Fiber Optic Tow Cable connector. The Slip Ring Assembly has 28
                electrical cables and   four fiber optic cables. The minimum electrical
                insulation requirement is 2M&#8486; at a voltage of 500 volts between all
                electrical conductors. The optical insertion loss should not exceed
                5.5dB at 1300nm.
              </para
  >
              <para>
                <figure>
                  <graphic
                  fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/fig_1_74.gif"
  ></graphic>
                  <figtitle>Fig. 1.74: Representation of Slip Ring Assembly</figtitle>
                </figure>
              </para>
            </content>
          </section>
          <section id="1.4.3.8 Slip Ring Junction Box SRJB" level="5">
            <title>1.4.3.8 Slip Ring Junction Box (SRJB)</title>
            <content>

              <para>
                See Fig. 1.75 for
                the location of SRJB.
              </para>
              <para>
                Electrical and optical signals coming
                from slip ring assembly and cables coming from the plinth (J2, J3,
                and J4) are connected to each other correspondingly through terminal
                strips inside the slip ring junction box.
              </para>
              <para>
