              </para>
            </content>
            <section id="1.4.3.10.1 Control Card" level="6">
              <title>1.4.3.10.1 Control Card</title>
              <content>

                <para>
                  The control card consists
                  of the following main blocks:
                </para>
                <para>
                  <ol type="a">
                    <li>
                      CPU: The CPU card is built around the 16-bit microcontroller (PIC24FJ128GC010)
                      with 64 IO, 2 UART ports and 3.3volt operated high frequency controller.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      RS485 convertors: It is a serial port used for communication.
                      It converts TTL to RS485 bus convertor with isolated stages, which
                      isolates TTL side from RS485.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Display Driving: It is an 8 digit 7 segment common anode red LED
                      display. They are grouped in two 4 digit sections. Each section can
                      be used to display numerical data 0000 to 9999. It also uses two 8
                      bit latches to facilitate 8 bit port as segment and control scanning
                      digit logic.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Encoder interface: Encoder is isolated and converted to 3.3 volt
                      level and square wave to narrow width pulses to convert usable as
                      interrupt interface.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Interface connectors: This section is used to connect CPU board
                      to interface card. Through these connectors, CPU interfaces with field
                      IO and RS485 bus.
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </para>
              </content>
            </section>
            <section id="1.4.3.10.2 Interface Card" level="6">
              <title>1.4.3.10.2 Interface Card</title>
              <?Pub Caret -2?>
              <content>
                <para>
                  This card acts as isolator in field and CPU. It consists
                  of following main blocks:
                </para>
                <para>
                  <ol type="a">
                    <li>
                      Power supply section: This section receives 24VDC from SMPS. It
                      converts 24 VDC supply to 3.3V and 12V. 3.3V supply is used for PIC
                      controller and 12V supply for cam limit switch.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Digital Input Section:  This section isolates 24VDC inputs and
                      converts it into 3.3 TTL levels that can be sensed by microcontroller.
                      Opto-isolation has electric interference reduction circuit.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Digital output: This section converts TTL outputs from CPU to
                      24VDC level and can be used as field interface. Opto-isolation has
                      electric interference reduction circuit.
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </para>
              </content>
            </section>
          </section>
        </section>
        <section id="1.4.4 Console" level="4">
          <title>1.4.4 Console</title>
          <content>
            <para>
              <h6>Introduction</h6>
              <para>
                For Introduction to Console,
                <a onclick="javascript:parent.VideoFrame(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Video/videos/V2_intro_console.mp4&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;" actuate="uSer">
                  Click here <img src="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/video.gif" style="height:40px;width:50px;" />
                </a>
              </para>
            </para>
            <para>
              A pictorial view
              of the Console is shown in Fig. 1.82.
            </para>
            <para>
              The Console is bulkhead
              mounted; it provides the man-machine interface and displays all information.
              The system collects acoustic data from the ocean environment and processes
              it. Processed data is made available to the System Operator and Officer
              of the Watch (OOW) in visual and audible form on the console. With
              the assistance of the System Operator the system is able to propose
              defensive actions to be taken by the ship in the face of a detected
              threat. Such defensive actions may be composed of passive countermeasures
              or a range of active countermeasures.
            </para>
            <para>
              Input supply to
              this unit is 115 VAC, 50/60Hz, 1&#8709; or 380V/415V/450VAC 50Hz/60Hz, 3&#8709;,
              from the ships mans. Data is exchanged between the console and the
              Cabinet sub-system through a communication link. Cooling is provided
              by a fan, operating on 12V. The console has the following capabilities:
            </para
  >

            <para>(a) Manual command and data entry facilities.</para>
            <para>
              (b) Audible non-voice outputs (audible warnings) and audible acoustic
              outputs.
            </para>
            <para>(c) Display of error and status reports.</para>

            <para>
              <figure>
                <graphic
                fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/fig_1_82.gif"
  ></graphic>
                <figtitle>Fig. 1.82: Pictorial view of Console</figtitle>
              </figure>
            </para>
            <para>
              <h6>Features</h6>
            </para>
            <para>
              The features of
              the console are as follows:
            </para>

            <para>(a) Intel Mobile Core i5, Dual-core Processor, 4GB Memory and Solid-State-Drive.</para>
            <para>(b) 20.1” LCD Display with Touch-screen and Mouse Pointer Device.</para>
            <para>(c) Selectable 3-phase or 1-phase AC power input.</para>
            <para>(d) Audio Output on Headphone and Built-in Speakers.</para>
            <para>(e) FO Ethernet port for external communication.</para>
            <para>(f) Pre-installed with “Windows 7 64 Bit Professional” Operating System.</para>

            <para>
              <h6>Controls and Indicators</h6>
            </para>
            <para>
              See
              Fig. 1.83 and Table-11 for Front panel Controls &amp; Indicators on
              Console
            </para>
            <para>
              <figure>
                <graphic
                fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/fig_1_83.gif"
  ></graphic>
                <figtitle>Fig. 1.83: Pictorial view of Console</figtitle>
              </figure>
            </para>
            <para>
