					  <section id="2.2.14.5 Fairlead Assembly" level="5">
						  <title>2.2.14.5 Fairlead Assembly</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  For correct installation of the Fairlead with plinth,
								  the following factors must be taken into consideration:
							  </para>

							  <para>(a) Safe and easy access for maintenance purposes. </para>
							  <para>
								  (b)
								  In order to achieve correct orientation, the plinth and its surrounding
								  area should not be obstructed with the metallic objects.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  (c)
								  No loose materials, components or swarf shall be permitted within
								  the winch housings before the plinth is welded.
							  </para>
							  <para>(d) Repaint the interior surface of the Fairlead Plinth prior installation. </para>
							  <para>
								  (e)
								  The metalwork shall be suitably cleaned and prepared before any
								  welding takes place.
							  </para>

							  <para>
								  <h6>Location</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  The fairlead shall
								  be mounted on the fairlead plinth such that the center of the fairlead
								  must be in line with the center of the Winch drum. The fairlead shall
								  be fitted on the stern of the ship (with larger opening facing the
								  sea). The area between the fairlead and center of the winch drum shall
								  not be obstructed with any metallic objects.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>
									  Installation
									  Procedure-Fairlead Assembly (With Plinth)
								  </h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  The pictorial
								  view of Fairlead is shown in Fig. 2.20. The Fairlead assembly is assembled
								  on its plinth and is installed on the ship as follows:
							  </para>

							  <para>
								  (a)
								  Lift the Fairlead Assembly (with Plinth) using Crane of capacity
								  greater than 2 ton, by attaching Type D-Shackle to two eyebolts (Size:
								  M12) and place the assembly at desired location on the deck end of
								  the ship.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  (b)
								  Ensure that Fairlead plinth bottom side should be painted but
								  welded surface should not be painted (at approximately 50 mm from
								  bottom side)<para>
									  <figure>
										  <graphic fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/fig_2_20.gif"></graphic>
										  <figtitle>Fig. 2.20: View of Fairlead</figtitle>
									  </figure>
								  </para>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  (c)
								  The welding of plinth onto the deck end surface to be carried
								  out as per AWS D1.1 or as per ship standard procedure by a qualified
								  welder. (Material of Construction of plinth - SS316; Rib Thickness
								  - 25 mm)
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  (d)
								  Post welding, Dye Penetration (DP) test to be carried out at all
								  welded joints to detect the defects. If no weld defect found, the
								  surface shall be painted with RAL 7042
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  (e)
								  Connect the source of fresh water to the Fairlead (Nipple size:
								  1” BSPT/NPT). Quarter opening of the valve delivers adequate volume
								  of water to wash the incoming tow
							  </para>

							  <para>
								  <note>
									  <para style="color:red">
										  Note:	After installation, operate the ball valve and check the
										  water flow. Ensure that 	all three nozzles cover the width of the
										  Fairlead.
									  </para>
								  </note>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
				  </section>
