						  <para>
							  <note>
								  <para style="color:red">Prior to usage of test equipments ensure that they are calibrated. </para>
							  </note>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <h6>Test Setup</h6>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  The test setup
							  is shown in Fig. 2.3<a
onclick="javascript:parent.showPDF(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/2_6_2_fig_2_3.pdf&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;"
actuate="user">click here</a>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <figure>
								  <graphic fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/sec_2_6_2gif.gif"></graphic>
								  <figtitle>Fig. 2.3: Test Setup-EDL</figtitle>
							  </figure>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <h6>Tests </h6>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  The following are
							  the tests carried out on the EDL:
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <ol type="1">
								  <li>Earth Bonding Check – EDL</li>
								  <li>Earth Bonding Check – RCU</li>
								  <li>Connector Bonding Check – EDL (Port/Stbd)</li>
								  <li>Connector Bonding Check – RCU</li>
								  <li>Isolation Test (115VAC, 1&#8709; or 380-450VAC, 3&#8709;) – EDL</li>
								  <li>Isolation Test (115VAC, 1&#8709; or 380 - 450VAC, 3&#8709;) – RCU</li>
								  <li>Leakage Current through ground conductor – EDL</li>
								  <li>Leakage Current through ground conductor – RCU</li>
								  <li>Inrush Current 115V 50Hz input - EDL (Port) (FAI)</li>
								  <li>Inrush Current 380V 50Hz input - EDL (Port) (FAI)</li>
								  <li>Inrush Current 115V, 50Hz input - RCU (FAI)</li>
