							  </ol>
						  </para>
					  </content>
					  <section id="2.6.2.1 Earth Bonding Check  EDL" level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.1 Earth Bonding Check – EDL</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  The test is performed to measure the resistance between
								  the prime earth and the Launcher earth points. The resistance must
								  also be measured between the prime earth and the earth point at the
								  EDL power connector. The resistance between the test point and the
								  prime earth stud shall be &lt; 0.1 Ohms.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Equipment </h6
  >
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  The following are the test equipments and accessories
								  required:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Digital Earth Resistance Meter.</li>
									  <li>Digital Stop Watch. </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Setup</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  The test setup is
								  shown in Fig. 2.4
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <figure>
									  <graphic fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/sec_2_6_2_1.gif"></graphic>
									  <figtitle>Fig. 2.4: Test Setup for Earth Bonding Check</figtitle>
								  </figure>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Procedure</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Perform
								  the following:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>
										  Connect the Green colour Probe between E of the Earth Resistance
										  Meter and Reference earthed electrode
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Connect the two Red colour Probe from (P) and (C) of the Earth
										  Resistance Meter to the Earthed electrode under test.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Switch ON the Digital Earth Resistance Meter. Set the rotary switch
										  to 20&#8486; resistance range.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Start the digital stop watch and wait for 60 sec, then record
										  the reading displayed on the Earth Resistance Meter Display, in Test
										  Data Record (TDR)-2.1.
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
