											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
									  </tbody>
								  </table>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
					  <section id="2.6.2.3 Connector Bonding Check EDL Port Stbd  " level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.3 Connector Bonding Check – EDL (Port/Stbd)  </title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  This test is performed to measure the resistance between
								  the prime earth stud and all panel mount connectors. The impedance
								  between the test point and the prime earth stud shall be &lt; 0.1
								  ohm.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Equipment: </h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  The following
								  are the test equipments and accessories required:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol
					  type="a">
									  <li>Digital Earth Resistance Meter.</li>
									  <li>Digital Stop Watch.</li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Setup</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  For test setup,(<a
	onclick="javascript:parent.showPDF(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/2_6_2_1_Earth_Bonding_Check_EDL.pdf&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;"
	actuate="user">
									  Click here.<img src="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/book.jfif" style="height:40px;width:50px;" />
								  </a>)

							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Procedure</h6
  >
							  </para>
							  <para>Perform the following:</para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>
										  Connect the Green colour Probe between E of the Earth Resistance
										  Meter and Reference earthed electrode.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Connect the two Red colour Probe from (P) and (C) of the Earth
										  Resistance Meter to the Earthed electrode under test
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Switch ON the Digital Earth Resistance Meter. Set the rotary switch
										  to 20&#8486; resistance range
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Start the digital stop watch and wait for 60 sec and then record
										  the reading displayed on Earth Resistance Meter Display, in TDR-2.3.
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>TDR-2.3: Connector Bonding Check – EDL (Port)</h6
  >
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <table frame="box" rules="all">
									  <colgroup>
										  <col/>
										  <col/>
										  <col/>
										  <col/>
										  <col/>
										  <col/>
									  </colgroup>
									  <tbody>
										  <tr>
											  <td align="center" rowspan="2">
												  <h6>Sl. No.</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td align="center" rowspan="2">
												  <h6>Resistance at point</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td align="center" colspan="2">
												  <h6>PORT EDL</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td align="center" colspan="2">
												  <h6>STBD EDL</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td align="center">
												  <h6>Result</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td align="center">
												  <h6>Pass/Fail</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td align="center">
												  <h6>Result</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td align="center">
												  <h6>Pass/Fail</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>1</td>
											  <td colspan="5">Local Control Unit</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td rowspan="6"></td>
											  <td>a)	Feedback 1 Connector</td>
											  <td></td>
