					  <section id="2.6.2.5 Isolation Test 115VAC 1 or 380 450VAC 3EDL "
					  level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.5 Isolation Test (115VAC, 1&#8709; or 380-450VAC, 3&#8709;) – EDL </title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  The isolation test is performed to verify whether a
								  specified level of isolation resistance is met or not. The Line isolation
								  shall be measured from the prime earth stud to the primary voltage
								  conductors using a Megger Tester. This should be measured at the prime
								  power input point connector. The line isolation measured shall be
								  >1M Ohm.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>
										  Measure the input isolation between Phase 1 (115VAC) by connecting
										  it to Megger Red probe and EDL prime Earth connected to Megger black
										  probe.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Connect the other end of megger Red Probe to (+) and Black Probe
										  to (-) on the Megger.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Switch ON Megger, select Megger range to 500V and start the Digital
										  Stop Watch
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Observe and record the reading after 60 sec on digital stop watch.
										  The line isolation shall be > 1M Ohm. Record the results obtained
										  in TDR-2.5.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Measure the input isolation between Phase 2 (115VAC) and Earth
										  as per procedure mentioned above and record the results obtained in
										  TDR-2.5(a).
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Measure the input isolation between Phase 1 (380VAC-450VAC) and
										  Earth, Phase 2 (380VAC-450VAC) and Earth, and Phase 3 (380VAC-450VAC)
										  and Earth as per procedure mentioned above. Record the results obtained
										  in TDR-2.5(b).
									  </li>
