					  <section id="2.6.2.9 Inrush Current 115V 50Hz input  EDL Port FAI"
					  level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.9 Inrush Current 115V 50Hz input - EDL (Port) (FAI)</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  The purpose of this test is to measure the inrush current
								  drawn at the power connector when primary power 115V, 50Hz, 1&#8709; is
								  applied. The inrush current shall be measured on each of the live
								  phases into the EDL at the power connector.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>
									  Test
									  Setup
								  </h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>The test setup is shown in Fig. 2.6.</para
  >
							  <para>
								  <figure>
									  <graphic fileref="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/sec_2_6_2_9.gif"></graphic>
									  <figtitle>Fig. 2.6: Test Setup – Inrush Current</figtitle>
								  </figure>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6> Test Procedure</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Perform
								  the following:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>
										  Primary power to the EDL during testing shall be 115V, 50Hz (1
										  Phase).
									  </li>
									  <li>Rotate or Wind 3 Turns on Phase Line</li>
									  <li>Switch ON DSO and press ‘Auto’ button on DSO to Calibrate DSO.</li>
									  <li>
										  Connect DSO Channel 1 Probe to Current Transformer with Resistor.
										  Switch ON DSO. Set time duration on 10 msecs and press Single button
										  on DSO to view the waveform, check maximum Peak voltage on DSO. Note
										  down the readings in TDR-2.9.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Repeat procedure given above for 115V, 50Hz (2 Phase) and record
										  the results obtained in TDR-2.9.
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6> TDR-2.9</h6>
								  <h6>
									  (Inrush Current 115V
									  50Hz input - EDL (Port))
								  </h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <table frame="box" rules="all">
									  <colgroup>
										  <col/>
										  <col/>
										  <col/>
									  </colgroup>
									  <tbody>
										  <tr>
											  <td colspan="2">
												  <h6>PORT EDL</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <h6>STBD EDL</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td></td>
											  <td>Inrush Current  (115 VAC) Live 1</td>
											  <td>Inrush Current  (115 VAC) Live 1</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>Results</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
									  </tbody>
								  </table>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <table frame="box" rules="all">
									  <colgroup>
										  <col/>
										  <col/>
										  <col/>
									  </colgroup>
									  <tbody>
										  <tr>
											  <td colspan="2">
												  <h6>PORT EDL</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <h6>STBD EDL</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td></td>
											  <td>Inrush Current  (115 VAC) Live 2</td>
											  <td>Inrush Current  (115 VAC) Live 2</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>Results</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
									  </tbody>
								  </table>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Formula to calculate Inrush Current:</h6
  >
							  </para>
							  <para>Available Value: Resistor: 47ohm</para>
							  <para>
								  Current
								  Transformer: 5A/0.1A; Ratio Factor: 5/0.1= 50
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Phase Line
								  Turns: 3 Turns.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Observed Maximum Peak Voltage on DSO:
								  V
							  </para>
							  <para>Inrush Current: I</para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Formula:</h6> Inrush
								  Current (Amp) I = (V/47) x (50/3).
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <note>
									  <para style="color:red">The procedure given above shall be adopted for testing EDL (STBD).</para>
								  </note>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
