					  <section id="2.6.2.14 FVA Charging" level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.14 FVA Charging</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  The objective of this test is to charge 10 FVAs fitted
								  in one EDL in less than 1 minute.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Equipment</h6
  >
							  </para>
							  <para>The following are the test equipment required:</para
  >
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Air charging cylinder with mating half connected (IRB14 male).</li>
									  <li>Firing valve assembly.</li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Procedure</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Carry out the
								  following:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>
										  Connect the external air charging cylinder with the mating half
										  connected (IRB14 male) to the EDL quick released coupling.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Open the air release valve of the external air charging cylinder
										  slowly.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Rotate the 4-way valve from SAFE to CHARGE position on the FVA
										  and record the time it takes to charge.
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
					  <section id="2.6.2.15 Vent Test" level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.15 Vent Test</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  The purpose of this test is to check whether the air
								  from the FVA is passing out into the atmosphere.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>
									  Test
									  Equipment
								  </h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>The following are the test equipment required</para
  >
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Charged FVA</li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Procedure</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Carry out the
								  following:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>
										  It is recommended that before venting the FVA, shut down the power
										  of the LCU or put LCU in SAFE mode.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  On FVA’s, rotate the 4-way valve knob to VENT position from its
										  current position.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  The venting air is passed through the respective vent pipe to
										  the atmosphere.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  After venting, rotate the 4-way valve knob to the safe position
										  mark on FVA.
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
					  <section id="2.6.2.16 Transmission Test" level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.16 Transmission Test</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  The purpose of this test is to check whether the EDL
								  is capable of transmitting its status at 1 second interval unconditionally
								  whenever it is powered and running.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Equipment</h6
  >
							  </para>
							  <para>The following are the test equipment required:</para
  >
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Laptop loaded with Status Display Software Version_1.4</li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Procedure</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Carry out the
								  following:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Ensure that power supply to the LCU is switched OFF. </li>
									  <li>
										  Connect the laptop at the open end of the communication cable
										  assembly (MDNS-62-02-03-06-007 &amp; MDNS-62-02-03-06-016).
									  </li>
									  <li>Open the Status Software and Power ON the LCU.</li>
									  <li>
										  Put SAFE/ENABLE switch to ENABLE position on the LCU, observe
										  the same on the Status Software.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM in LOCAL ARM on the LCU, observe that
										  the same appears on the Status Software.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM in REMOTE, observe that the same appears
										  on the Status Software.
									  </li>
									  <li>By default, 4-way switch of all FVAs is in SAFE Position.</li>
									  <li>
										  Put 4-way switch of any FVA from SAFE to ARM and observe the same
										  in the Status Software.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put 4-way switch of any FVA from SAFE to VENT and observe the
										  same in the Status Software.
									  </li>
									  <li>Put 4-way switch of ALL FVAs to SAFE position.</li>
									  <li>On LCU, put SAFE/ENABLE switch to SAFE position.</li>
									  <li>On LCU, put REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM to SAFE position.</li>
									  <li>
										  Now, check and confirm the following parameters for functionality: <para
  >
											  <ol type="i">
												  <li>RS 485 Signal</li>
												  <li>Frame rate</li>
												  <li>Baud rate / data rate</li>
												  <li>Frame structure</li>
											  </ol>
										  </para>
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
					  <section id="2.6.2.17 Functional Test" level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.17 Functional Test</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  This test is carried out to check if the system is
								  functioning properly.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>
									  Test Equipment &amp; Software
									  required
								  </h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  The following are the test equipment &amp;
								  software required:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>EAD assembled in EDL barrels</li>
									  <li>Laptop with Status Software Version_1.4</li>
									  <li>Laptop with Autofire Test Software Version_1.0</li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Procedure</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Carry out the
								  following:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Switch ON the LCU and RCU</li>
									  <li>Start Digital Stop Watch</li>
									  <li>Put all FVAs in ARM mode</li>
									  <li>On the LCU, put SAFE-ENABLE key switch to ENABLE</li>
									  <li>On the RCU, put AUTO-MANUAL key switch to AUTO</li>
									  <li>Stop Digital Stop watch</li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Read or Observe the time required to do above steps.
								  (It should be less than 1 minute)
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
					  <section id="2.6.2.18 Sounder Activation Test" level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.18 Sounder Activation Test</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  This test is carried out to check whether the sounder
								  activates at the time of device launching.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Procedure</h6
  >
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  The EDL incorporates a sounder which is activated when
								  the following conditions are met:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  (a)	<h6>
									  Under LOCAL
									  Control:
								  </h6><para>
									  <ol type="i">
										  <li>The LCU, on the EDL in use, is switched ON</li>
										  <li>SAFE/ENABLE switch, on the EDL in use, is set to ENABLE.</li>
										  <li>
											  LOCAL ARM/SAFE/REMOTE switch, on the EDL in use, is set to LOCAL
											  ARM.<para>
												  <warning>
													  <para>
														  <h6>Warning: Do NOT press barrel Firing Button</h6>
													  </para>
												  </warning>
											  </para>
										  </li>
									  </ol>
								  </para>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  (b)	<h6>Under REMOTE Control:</h6><para>
									  <ol
						type="i">
										  <li>The LCU, on the EDL in use, is switched ON</li>
										  <li>SAFE/ENABLE switch, on the EDL in use, is set to ENABLE</li>
										  <li>LOCAL ARM/SAFE/REMOTE switch, on the EDL in use, is set to REMOTE</li>
										  <li>RCU is switched ON</li>
										  <li>AUTO/MANUAL switch, on the RCU in use, is set to AUTO.</li>
										  <li>
											  REMOTE ARM/SAFE/AUTO ARM” switch, on the RCU in use, is set to
											  REMOTE ARM.<para>
												  <warning>
													  <para>
														  <h6>Warning: Do NOT press barrel Firing Button</h6>
													  </para>
												  </warning>
											  </para>
										  </li>
									  </ol>
								  </para>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  (c)	<h6>Under Cabinet Control</h6><ol type="i">
									  <li>LCU, on the EDL in use, is Switched ON.</li>
									  <li>SAFE/ENABLE switch, on the EDL in use, is set to ENABLE.</li>
									  <li>LOCAL-ARM/SAFE/REMOTE switch, on the EDL in use, is set to REMOTE.</li>
									  <li>RCU is Switched ON.</li>
									  <li>On the RCU, set AUTO/MANUAL switch to AUTO.</li>
									  <li>EAD need to be present in the Barrel.</li>
									  <li>Set the FVA that present in the Barrel to ARM position.</li>
									  <li>Put remaining FVAs in SAFE Position.</li>
									  <li>Remove EAD and introduce resistor to safeguard.</li>
									  <li>Put FVA to be in ARM position. </li>
									  <li>
										  The REMOTE ARM/SAFE/AUTO ARM, on the RCU in use, is set to AUTO
										  ARM.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Make an announcement in the broadcast; inform the duty staff and
										  all the personnel concerned for clearing the area.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Sounder to sound and subsequently FVA to fire. Sounder shall be
										  permitted to be reconfigured only by the authorized personnel.
									  </li>
									  <li>Put all FVA in SAFE position after completion of test.</li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
					  <section id="2.6.2.19 EAD Type Identification Test-EDL Port" level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.19 EAD Type Identification Test-EDL (Port)</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Equipment &amp; Software required</h6>
							  </para
  >
							  <para>The following are the test equipment &amp; software required:</para
  >
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>EAD Test Jig</li>
									  <li>Laptop with Status Software Version_1.4</li>
									  <li>Digital Stop Watch</li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Procedure </h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Carry out the
								  following:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Put the EAD Test Jig in one FVA.</li>
									  <li>Connect or Put EAD Type Test Jig in any one of FVA.</li>
									  <li>
										  Select or rotate Selector Switch for selection of EAD Type. EAD
										  Test Jig contains 10 positions EAD Type as given below:<para>
											  <ol
							type="i">
												  <li>Position 1: Short Circuit</li>
												  <li>Position 2: Type 1</li>
												  <li>Position 3: Type 2</li>
												  <li>Position 4: Type 3</li>
												  <li>Position 5: Type 4</li>
												  <li>Position 6: Type 5</li>
												  <li>Position 7: Type 6</li>
												  <li>Position 8: Type 7</li>
												  <li>Position 9: Type 8</li>
												  <li>Position 10: Open Circuit</li>
											  </ol>
										  </para>
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put the selector switch of EAD Test Jig on Position 1 (Short Circuit)
										  and verify that the EAD Type on the status software is identified
										  as Short Circuit.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put the selector switch of EAD Test Jig on Position 2 (Type 1)
										  and verify that the EAD Type on the status software is identified
										  as Type 1.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put the selector switch of EAD Test Jig on Position 3 (Type 2)
										  and verify that the EAD Type on the status software is identified
										  as Type 2.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put the selector switch of EAD Test Jig on Position 4 (Type 3)
										  and verify that the EAD Type on the status software is identified
										  as Type 3.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put the selector switch of EAD Test Jig on Position 5 (Type 4)
										  and verify that the EAD Type on the status software is identified
										  as Type 4.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put the selector switch of EAD Test Jig on Position 6 (Type 5)
										  and verify that the EAD Type on the status software is identified
										  as Type 5.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put the selector switch of EAD Test Jig on Position 7 (Type 6)
										  and verify that the EAD Type on the status software is identified
										  as Type 6.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put the selector switch of EAD Test Jig on Position 8 (Type 7)
										  and verify that the EAD Type on the status software is identified
										  as Type 7.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put the selector switch of EAD Test Jig on Position 9 (Type 8)
										  and verify that the EAD Type on the status software is identified
										  as Type 8.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Put the selector switch of EAD Test Jig on Position 10 (Open Circuit)
										  and verify that the EAD Type on the status software is identified
										  as Open Circuit.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Observe the readings after 20 sec on Status software version no.
										  1.4 using Digital Stop watch. Record the readings in TDR-2.15.
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <note>
									  <para style="color:red">

										  Note:	Repeat the steps given above for the EAD Type Identification
										  Test on EDL (Stbd) and record the results obtained in TDR-2.16.

									  </para>
								  </note>
							  </para>
