					  <section id="2.6.2.20 EAD Launch Control from Local Fire" level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.20 EAD Launch Control from Local Fire</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  The purpose of this test is to check each Launch Barrel
								  position whether controllable from its own “Local Fire” button.
							  </para
  >
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Equipment &amp; Software required</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para
  >The following are the test equipment &amp; software required:</para
  >
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Firing Valves</li>
									  <li>Air Source</li>
									  <li>Laptop with Status Software Version_1.4</li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Setup</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Make a test setup
								  as shown in Fig. 2.3.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Procedure from Local Fire</h6
  >
							  </para>
							  <para>Carryout the following:</para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Ensure that 4-way key switch is in SAFE position.</li>
									  <li>
										  On LCU, ensure the following:<para>
											  <ol type="i">
												  <li>SAFE/ENABLE switch in SAFE position.</li>
												  <li>REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM switch in SAFE position.</li>
											  </ol>
										  </para>
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Connect EDL Power supply cable assembly to Power source designated
										  as J1.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Connect RCU Power supply cable assembly to Power source designated
										  as J5.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Once the power supply cables are connected white indicator lamps
										  (indicate the availability of power to the launcher) will glow on
										  LCU &amp; RCU.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Switch ON the LCU using Selector Valve and check that Power Ready
										  White LED is glowing.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Switch ON the RCU using Selector Valve and check that Power Ready
										  LED is glowing.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Charge the FVA 1-10 through charge position up to 90 bar for each
										  FVA.
									  </li>
									  <li>Once Charged, put FVA again on SAFE position.</li>
									  <li>Put EAD in charged barrel.</li>
									  <li>Put FVA in ARM position.</li>
									  <li>
										  On LCU, put SAFE/ENABLE key switch in ENABLE position.<para>
											  <warning>
												  <para>
													  <h6>Warning: Do NOT Press Fire Button on LCU</h6>
												  </para>
											  </warning>
										  </para>
									  </li>
									  <li>Available (AVL) indicator will start glowing. </li>
									  <li>
										  Turn LOCAL ARM/SAFE/REMOTE switch to Local ARM only to verify
										  Ready Indicator and confirm Ready indicator is glowing.<para>
											  <warning>
												  <para>
													  <h6>
														  Warning Do NOT Press Fire Button on LCU. It is only to verify
														  RDY (READY) indicator on LCU
													  </h6>
												  </para>
											  </warning>
										  </para>
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Remove EAD from Barrel for firing.<para>
											  <warning>
												  <para>
													  <h6>
														  Warning EDL READY TO FIRE. Make an announcement in the broadcast
														  for area clearance
													  </h6>
												  </para>
											  </warning>
										  </para>
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  LOCAL ARM/SAFE/REMOTE switch, on the EDL is set to LOCAL ARM by
										  one hand (which initiates sounder without ready indicator) and by
										  other hand press push button of respective barrel resulting into EAD
										  launch.
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
					  <section id="2.6.2.21 EAD Launch Control from Remote Fire" level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.21 EAD Launch Control from Remote Fire</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  The purpose of this test is to check each Launch Barrel
								  position whether controllable from its own “Remote Fire” button.
							  </para
  >
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Equipment &amp; Software required</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para
  >The following are the test equipment &amp; software required:</para
  >
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Firing Valves</li>
									  <li>Air Source</li>
									  <li>Laptop with Status Software Version_1.4</li>
									  <li>RCU</li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Setup</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  For test setup,(<a
	onclick="javascript:parent.showPDF(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/2_6_2_Expendable_Device_Launcher_EDL.pdf&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;"
	actuate="user">
									  Click here.<img src="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/book.jfif" style="height:40px;width:50px;" />
								  </a>)
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Procedure</h6
  >
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="i">
									  <li>Ensure that 4-way key switch is in SAFE position.</li>
									  <li>
										  On RCU, ensure the following:<para>
											  <ol type="i">
												  <li>SAFE/ENABLE switch in SAFE position.</li>
												  <li>3-way key switch ‘AUTO ARM/SAFE/REMOTE ARM’ in SAFE mode.</li>
											  </ol>
										  </para>
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Connect EDL Power supply cable assembly to Power source designated
										  as J1.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  (Connect RCU Power supply cable assembly to Power source designated
										  as J5.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Once the power supply cables are connected white indicator lamps
										  (indicate the availability of power to the launcher) will glow on
										  LCU &amp; RCU.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Switch ON the LCU using Selector Valve and check that Power Ready
										  White LED is glowing.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Switch ON the RCU using Selector Valve and check that Power Ready
										  LED is glowing.
									  </li>
									  <li>Charge the FVA through charge position up to 90 bar.</li>
									  <li>Once Charged, put FVA again on SAFE position.</li>
									  <li>Put EAD in charged barrel.</li>
									  <li>Put FVA in ARM position.</li>
									  <li>
										  On LCU, put SAFE/ENABLE switch in ENABLE position.<para>
											  <warning>
												  <para>
													  <h6>Warning: Do NOT Press Fire Button on LCU</h6>
												  </para>
											  </warning>
										  </para>
									  </li>
									  <li>Available (AVL) indicator will start glowing.</li>
									  <li>On EDL, set LOCAL ARM/SAFE/REMOTE switch to REMOTE.</li>
									  <li>On RCU put AUTO/MANUAL key switch to AUTO position. </li>
									  <li>
										  Available (AVL) indicator starts glowing as RCU getting status
										  of EDL viz., Communication line.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  On RCU, put REMOTE ARM/SAFE/AUTO ARM switch to REMOTE ARM only
										  to verify Ready (RDY) indicator.<para>
											  <warning>
												  <para>
													  <h6>
														  Warning Do NOT Press Fire Button. It is only to verify Ready
														  (RDY) indicator in RCU
													  </h6>
												  </para>
											  </warning>
										  </para>
									  </li>
									  <li>Put RCU in SAFE Position.</li>
									  <li>
										  Remove EAD from Barrel for firing.<para>
											  <warning>
												  <para>
													  <h6>
														  Warning EDL READY TO FIRE. Make an announcement in the broadcast
														  for area clearance
													  </h6>
												  </para>
											  </warning>
										  </para>
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  On RCU, set REMOTE ARM/SAFE/AUTO ARM switch to REMOTE ARM by one
										  hand (which initiates sounder without ready indicator) and by other
										  hand press fire push button of respective barrel resulting in EAD
										  launch. Each Fire button has to be pressed within 3 seconds from the
										  previous fire button that has pressed.
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
