					  <section id="2.6.2.22 Transmission Test from RCU to Cabinet" level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.22 Transmission Test from RCU to Cabinet</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  The purpose of this test is to check whether the RCU
								  is capable of transmitting its status to Cabinet.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6
  >Test Equipment</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  The following are the test equipment
								  required:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Laptop loaded with Status Display Software Version_1.4</li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Test Procedure</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  Carry out the
								  following:
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>Ensure that power supply to the LCU/RCU is switched OFF. </li>
									  <li>
										  Connect the laptop at the open end of the communication cable
										  assembly (MDNS-62-02-03-06-007 &amp; MDNS-62-02-03-06-016).
									  </li>
									  <li>Please provide data as explained for LCU</li>
									  <li>
										  Now, check and confirm the following parameters for functionality:<para
  >
											  <ol type="i">
												  <li>RS 485 Signal</li>
												  <li>Frame rate</li>
												  <li>Baud rate / data rate</li>
												  <li>Frame structure</li>
											  </ol>
										  </para>
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
					  <section id="2.6.2.23 Pneumatic Connections Test " level="5">
						  <title>2.6.2.23 Pneumatic Connections Test </title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  This test is to ensure all pneumatic connections are
								  airtight and all electrical connections are proper. The test is to
								  be carried out only when all 10 FVA’s are installed.
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <ol
					  type="a">
									  <li>
										  Install all 10 FVA’s and restore their pneumatic connections (Charge&amp;
										  Vent) and electrical connections (Fire Pulse Connector &amp; Feedback
										  Connector) with EDL.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Set the 5-way mechanical selector valve ‘SAFE/VENT/CHARGE/ARM’
										  to ‘CHARGE’.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Charge the FVA assembly to 20 bar (test pressure) by connecting
										  pneumatic supply to the Isolation Valve of EDL (tests to be carried
										  out in a controlled environment)
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Set the 5-way mechanical selector valve ‘SAFE/VENT/CHARGE/ARM’
										  to ‘SAFE’.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  Spray a soap water solution around the pneumatic plugs/joints
										  and check for any leakage. If a leak is detected, discharge the FVA
										  completely by setting the 5-way mechanical selector valve ‘SAFE/VENT/CHARGE/ARM’
										  to ‘VENT’.
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <note>
									  <para style="color:red">

										  Note:	Solenoid Operational Test &amp; Pressure Sensor Test
										  given above shall be carried out post integration of FVA on to the
										  EDL (which is fitted with LCU &amp; connected to RCU) by interpreting
										  the information displayed on the Console and by operating either from
										  LCU or RCU.

									  </para>
								  </note>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>

				  </section>
