					  <section id="2.6.3.1 Functional test of Firing circuit " level="5">
						  <title>2.6.3.1 Functional test of Firing circuit </title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  The pupose of this test is to check the firing circuit.
								  Before carrying out this test ensure that Charges are not inserted.
							  </para
  >
							  <para>
								  <table frame="box" rules="all">
									  <colgroup>
										  <col width="13*"/>
										  <col width="43*"/>
										  <col width="43*"/>
									  </colgroup>
									  <tbody>
										  <tr>
											  <td align="center">
												  <h6>Sl. No.</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td align="center">
												  <h6>Functional Description</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td align="center">
												  <h6>Requirement</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1</td>
											  <td>Connect power supply cable to the unit and switch ON mains. </td>
											  <td valign="top">“POWER AVL” LED ON</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>2</td>
											  <td>Switch ON “POWER ON”</td>
											  <td>“POWER ON” LED ON</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">3</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>Press “Lamp Test” push button switch.</para>
												  <para>
													  <note>
														  <para style="color:red">
															  Note: Ensure Charges are not inserted
														  </para>
													  </note>
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">All LED’s ON</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4</td>
											  <td>Make “SAFE-ENABLE” switch in “ENABLE” Mode</td>
											  <td valign="top">--</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">5</td>
											  <td>Make “REMOTE-SAFE-LOCAL ARM” switch in LOCAL ARM Mode.</td>
											  <td valign="top">--</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
