					  </section>
					  <section id="2.6.5.5 Main Control Panel MCP  " level="5">
						  <title>2.6.5.5 Main Control Panel (MCP) </title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  <table frame="box" rules="all">
									  <colgroup>
										  <col/>
										  <col/>
										  <col span="3"/>
									  </colgroup>
									  <tbody>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  <h6>Sl. No.</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <h6>Description</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td colspan="3">
												  <h6>Related documents</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>1</td>
											  <td>Main Control Panel (MCP)</td>
											  <td>
												  (<a
							 onclick="javascript:parent.showPDF(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/Plate_3_17.pdf&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;"
							 actuate="user">Wiring Diagram</a>)
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  (<a
							 onclick="javascript:parent.showPDF(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/Fig_5_33_HMI_Panel.pdf&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;"
							 actuate="user">GA</a>)
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  (<a
							 onclick="javascript:parent.showPDF(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/MCP_PL.pdf&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;"
							 actuate="user">PL</a>)
											  </td>
										  </tr>
									  </tbody>
								  </table>
							  </para>
							  >
							  <para>The functional test of the MCP is provided in the table below:</para
>
							  <para>
								  <h6>Functional Test –MCP</h6>
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <table frame="box"
						  rules="all">
									  <colgroup>
										  <col width="16*"/>
										  <col width="40*"/>
										  <col width="40*"/>
									  </colgroup>
									  <tbody>
										  <tr>
											  <td>Sl. No.</td>
											  <td>Functional Description</td>
											  <td>Requirement</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>1</td>
											  <td colspan="2">
												  The Winch utilizes 440V AC. All insulation and continuity
												  checks must be carried out before power cables are connected. Ensure
												  that all units of the Winch are properly connected and suitably grounded
												  before applying main power supply to the Winch.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>2</td>
											  <td>Switch ON the ship supply of the winch.</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator ON</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local and Remote indicator OFF </li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
														  <li>Green Indicator at Proximity Sensors ON.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>3</td>
											  <td>
												  Release the ‘Emergency Stop’ Switch and press ‘Emergency Reset’
												  Switch. Set the Standby / Operation Switch at Standby Position.
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local and Remote indicator OFF. </li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator displays previous stored value.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>3.1</td>
											  <td>Press the ‘Lamp Test’ Switch</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>All Indicators in ON position.</li>
														  <li>Render and remote Buzzer sounding.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth display indicates “8888”.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>3.2</td>
											  <td>Depress the ‘Lamp Test’ switch</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>All Indicators in initial position.</li>
														  <li>Render and remote Buzzer not sounding.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth display shows initial value”.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>3.3</td>
											  <td>Press the ‘Zero Dimmer’ Switch </td>
											  <td>
												  All indicators and Length and Depth display is in OFF condition,
												  though the MCP is in standby mode.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>3.4</td>
											  <td>Depress the ‘Zero Dimmer’ Switch</td>
											  <td>
												  All indicators and Length and Depth display is in ON condition
												  and shows current status.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>3.5</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>Press and Depress the Brightness control single switch.</para
>
												  <para>Repeat the above procedure in 5 steps of depress </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  Brightness of Tow Scope display decreases in five steps, on reaching
												  lowest brightness step, the display regains its maximum brightness
												  if further decreased.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>3.6</td>
											  <td>Set the Local / Remote Switch at Local Position</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indictor OFF</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local and Remote indicator OFF.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td rowspan="2">3.7</td>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Drum Joystick at Payout
												  direction.
											  </td>
											  <td>Drum not rotating.</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Drum Joystick at Haul in
												  Direction.
											  </td>
											  <td>Drum not rotating.</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td rowspan="2">3.8</td>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Level wind Joystick at
												  STBD direction.
											  </td>
											  <td>No displacement at Level Wind Assembly.</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Level Wind Joystick at
												  port Direction.
											  </td>
											  <td>No displacement at Level wind assembly.</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>3.9</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  Set the Local / Remote Switch at Remote Position and Remote
													  Not Connected.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Set the Local / Remote Switch at Remote
													  Position and Remote is Connected.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Move Drum Joystick and
													  Wind Level Joystick for operation
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local and Remote indicator OFF.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous value.</li>
														  <li>Drum not rotating by Joystick.</li>
														  <li>No displacement for Level Wind Assembly by joystick.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>3.10</td>
											  <td>Set the maintenance mode switch at maintenance   </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>System Ready Indicator blinking.</li>
														  <li>
															  Enables override of Over release stop and Excess Tow recovery
															  Switch
														  </li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>Set the Standby / Operation Switch at Operation Position.</para
>
												  <para>Set Local / Remote at Local.</para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Remote indicator OFF.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.1</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>Press the ‘Emergency Stop’ Switch.</para>
												  <para>
													  Move Drum
													  Joystick and Wind Level Joystick for operation
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator ON</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local indicator ON.</li>
														  <li>Remote indicator OFF.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
														  <li>Drum not rotating by Joystick.</li>
														  <li>No displacement for Level Wind Assembly by joystick.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.2</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  Release the Emergency Stop Switch and Press Emergency Reset
													  Switch
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Move Drum Joystick and Wind Level Joystick for
													  operation
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indictor ON</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local indicator ON.</li>
														  <li>Remote indicator OFF.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
														  <li>Drum rotates by Joystick.</li>
														  <li>Displacement for Level Wind Assembly by joystick.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.3</td>
											  <td>Press the ‘Lamp Test’ Switch</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>All Indicators in ON position.</li>
														  <li>Render and remote Buzzer sounding.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth display indicates “8888”.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.4</td>
											  <td>Depress the ‘Lamp Test’ switch</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>All Indicators in initial position.</li>
														  <li>Render and remote Buzzer not sounding.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth display shows initial value”.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.5</td>
											  <td>Press the ‘Zero Dimmer’ Switch </td>
											  <td>
												  All indicators and Length and Depth display is in OFF condition,
												  though the MCP is in standby mode.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.6</td>
											  <td>Depress the ‘Zero Dimmer’ Switch</td>
											  <td>
												  All indicators and Length and Depth display is in ON condition
												  and shows current status.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.7</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>Press and Depress the Brightness control single switch.</para
>
												  <para>
													  <h6>Repeat the above procedure in 5 steps of depresses.</h6
>
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  Brightness of Tow Scope display decreases in five steps on reaching
												  lowest brightness step, display regains its maximum brightness if
												  further decreased.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.8</td>
											  <td>Set the Local / Remote Switch at Local Position</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indictor ON</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local indicator ON </li>
														  <li>Remote indicator OFF.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td rowspan="2">4.9</td>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Drum Joystick at Payout
												  direction.
											  </td>
											  <td rowspan="2">
												  <para>Drum rotating in both directions.</para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Drum Joystick at Haul in
												  Direction.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td rowspan="2">4.10</td>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Level wind Joystick at
												  STBD direction.
											  </td>
											  <td rowspan="2">Displacement of Level wind Assembly is achieved.</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Level Wind Joystick at
												  port Direction.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.11</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Joystick at STBD
													  direction for Level Wind Assembly.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Travel Extreme Condition
													  of STBD direction.
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Displacement of Level wind Assembly is started.</li>
														  <li>
															  Green indicator on Proximity sensors at both end (STBD and PORT
															  side) is ON.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  Yellow indicator on Proximity sensors at both end (STBD and PORT
															  side) is OFF.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  Once it reaches inside operating area of Proximity Sensor (STBD
															  side) it will stop the displacement of Level Wind assembly towards
															  STBD direction. Displacement towards Port Side is Possible.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  After step (d), Proximity Sensor (STBD Side) Green indicator and
															  Yellow indicator are ON position.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  At Proximity Sensor (PORT Side) Green indicator ON and Yellow
															  indicator in OFF position.
														  </li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.12</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Joystick at PORT
													  direction for Level Wind Assembly.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Travel Extreme Condition
													  of PORT direction.
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Displacement of Level wind Assembly is started.</li>
														  <li>
															  Green indicator on Proximity sensors at both end (STBD and PORT
															  side) is ON.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  Yellow indicator on Proximity sensors at both end (STBD and PORT
															  side) is OFF.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  Once it reaches inside operating area of Proximity Sensor (PORT
															  side) it will stop the displacement of Level Wind assembly towards
															  PORT direction. Displacement towards STBD Side is Possible.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  After step (d), Proximity Sensor (PORT Side) Green indicator and
															  Yellow indicator are ON position.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  At Proximity Sensor (STBD Side) Green indicator ON and Yellow
															  indicator in OFF position.
														  </li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.13</td>
