				  <section id="2.6.6 Fairlead " level="4">
					  <title>2.6.6 Fairlead </title>
					  <content>
						  <para>
							  The purpose of this test is to remove dirt, gravel
							  and other foreign material clogs in the nozzle/shower. Under most
							  operating conditions, manufacturer recommends half-yearly inspection
							  on nozzle/shower pipe as given below:
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <ol type="a">
								  <li>
									  Shut off the main valve connected between the fresh water supply
									  source and shower inlet pipe.
								  </li>
								  <li>
									  Remove all nozzle caps, clean rust or corrosion inside the nozzle
									  area.
								  </li>
								  <li>Put back the nozzle caps. </li>
								  <li>
									  Open the fresh water supply source hydrant valve (fully open position
									  to allow water pressure) and see if rocks or other foreign material
									  flush out of the nozzles. Flush water for several minutes and check
									  for any leakages.
								  </li>
								  <li>
									  If flushing does not solve the problem it would indicate that
									  something is trapped in the shower pipe. Replace the shower pipe.
								  </li>
							  </ol>
						  </para>
					  </content>
				  </section>
				  <section id="2.6.7 Console " level="4">
					  <title>2.6.7 Console </title>
					  <content>
						  >
						  <para>
							  For Console AC-DC Power Connection Details,(<a
onclick="javascript:parent.showPDF(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/Plate_4_1.pdf&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;"
