>
						  <para>
							  For Console USB/Serial Connection Details,(<a
onclick="javascript:parent.showPDF(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/Plate_4_5.pdf&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;"
actuate="user">
								  Click here.<img src="../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/book.jfif" style="height:40px;width:50px;" />
							  </a>)
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  The console provides the
							  man-machine interface and displays all information.
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  The
							  following tests are carried out:
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <ol type="1">
								  <li>Rugged LCD Display Test</li>
								  <li>Power Supply Module (NPSW240-12) Test</li>
								  <li>Power Supply Module (NPSM240-12) Test</li>
								  <li>Keypad Test</li>
								  <li>DC Fan Test</li>
								  <li>EMI Filters</li>
							  </ol>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <h6>Test equipment and accessories required</h6
>
						  </para>
						  <para>Following are the test equipment and accessories required:</para
>
						  <para>
							  <ol type="1">
								  <li>Power Supply Unit (24 VDC)</li>
								  <li>Cables Set</li>
								  <li>Multimeter</li>
							  </ol>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <h6>Rugged LCD Display Test</h6>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  Connect
							  all interface cables to the LCD Display in the system. With the help
							  of diagnostic software, check if the display in terms of color, contrast,
							  brightness, sharpness, resolution, position, display size, etc is
							  proper.
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <h6>Power Supply Module (NPSW240-12) Test  </h6
>
						  </para>
						  <para>Carry out the following:</para>
						  <para>
							  <ol type="a">
								  <li>
									  Connect the power supply cable that provides 380-500 VAC supply
									  to the input of the power supply module. (Input connection: 3 phase,
									  L to L).
								  </li>
								  <li>Switch ON the power supply.</li>
								  <li>Check that voltage at output connection is 12 V DC.</li>
							  </ol>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <h6>Power Supply Module (NPSM240-12) Test  </h6
>
						  </para>
						  <para>Carry out the following:</para>
						  <para>
							  <ol type="a">
								  <li>
									  Connect the power supply cable that provides 115V AC to the input
									  of the power supply module. (Input connection: Single phase, L to
									  L).
								  </li>
								  <li>Switch ON the power supply.</li>
								  <li>Check that voltage at output connection is 12 V DC.  </li>
							  </ol>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <h6>Keypad Test  </h6>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  The keypad test
							  is carried out to check whether it is functioning properly.
						  </para
>
						  <para>
							  a)	Attach the keypad to the computer and test it with help
							  of diagnostic software. Under other option select following tests:
						  </para>
						  <para>‘Keyboard press test for testing all the keys’</para
>
						  <para>
							  <h6>DC Fan Test  </h6>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  The purpose of this test
							  is to check if the fans are operating correctly.
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <ol
					  type="a">
								  <li>
									  Connect the cable that provides power supply 12VDC at the input
									  terminals.
								  </li>
								  <li>Switch ON the power supply.</li>
								  <li>Verify that fan is working correctly.</li>
							  </ol>
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <h6>EMI Filters Test</h6>
							  <?Pub Caret -2?>
						  </para
>
						  <para>
							  The purpose of this test is to check if the EMI Filter is functioning
							  properly.
						  </para>
						  <para>
							  <ol type="a">
								  <li>
									  Apply the respective power supply (AC/DC) at the input terminals
									  of the filter.
								  </li>
								  <li>
									  Measure the output at the output terminals. It should be same
									  as the input.
								  </li>
							  </ol>
						  </para>
					  </content>
				  </section>
