				  <section id="2.7.4 NTDS Integrated Tests" level="4">
					  <title>2.7.4 NTDS Integrated Tests</title>
					  <section id="2.7.4.1 Launcher Test" level="5">
						  <title>2.7.4.1 Launcher Test</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  <table frame="box" rules="all">
									  <colgroup>
										  <col width="14*"/>
										  <col width="20*"/>
										  <col width="20*"/>
										  <col width="21*"/>
										  <col width="21*"/>
									  </colgroup>
									  <tbody>
										  <tr>
											  <td rowspan="2">
												  <h6>Test Id</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td rowspan="2">
												  <h6>Test</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td rowspan="2">
												  <h6>Requirement</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td colspan="2">
												  <h6>Observation</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  <h6>Status</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <h6>TBC</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>1</td>
											  <td colspan="4">
												  <h6>Launcher Charging</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.1</td>
											  <td>Ensure Launcher barrels are loaded with an EAD as required</td>
											  <td valign="top">EAD present at required location</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.2</td>
											  <td>Ensure 5-way switch on SAFE position on each firing valve</td>
											  <td valign="top">5-way switch positioned on SAFE position</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.3</td>
											  <td>
												  Remove the SAFE/ENABLE key and the REMOTE / SAFE / LOCAL ARM key
												  from the LCU
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">Absence of Keys on LCU</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.4</td>
											  <td>
												  Ensure on the Launcher the Charge Line Discharge Valve is  in
												  the Closed (Isolation) position
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">Charge line Discharge Valve in closed position</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.5</td>
											  <td>
												  Connect the compressed air charging source. Ensure the charging
												  source has a compressed air pressure sufficient to support an 90
												  bar charge being achieved.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">90 bar on Pressure Gauge</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.6</td>
											  <td>
												  Ensure on the charging source that any Shut off and Bleed off
												  valves are closed
											  </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.7</td>
											  <td>
												  Connect the Charging Line of the Charging source to the connector
												  in the Launcher
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">Connection of Charging Line with connector in Launcher</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.8</td>
											  <td>
												  Ensure the charging line has engaged correctly with the charging
												  quick connector, and the locking ring is engaged fully forward.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">Proper Connection </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.9</td>
											  <td>
												  Slowly open the charging source shut off valve, an audible sound
												  will be heard and then cease as air charges the pressure lines and
												  stabilises within the Launcher.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">Charging of the Valve </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.10</td>
											  <td>
												  Listen out for any major leakages. If leaks are found STOP charging
												  and shut off the valve on the charging source, then discharge the
												  charge line by opening the charge line discharge valve slowly. Investigate
												  source of leak before proceeding. (Detailed leak test shall be performed)
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">No leakage present</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.11</td>
											  <td>
												  On Barrel 1 rotate slowly the 5-way valve from SAFE to CHARGE
												  position. Monitor the pressure gauge upto it reaches 90 bar  and then
												  rotate the 4 way switch to SAFE position once 90 bar pressure is achieved.
												  (The preset of pressure relief valve and inline pressure reducer prevents
												  the system from excess charging)
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">Position of 5-way switch to CHARGE position</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.12</td>
											  <td>Repeat the above step 1.11 for rest of the barrels.</td>
											  <td valign="top">Same as above 1.11</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.13</td>
											  <td>
												  Verify barrels required are charged to 90 bar pressure. When all
												  barrels are at 90 bar pressure, ensure all 5-way switch of all barrels
												  are at SAFE position.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  Pressure in Reservoir 90 bar and 5-way switch positioned
												  on SAFE position
											  </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1.14</td>
											  <td>
												  Close the Shut off valve on the charging source and the Open the
												  Bleed Off Valve on the charging source slowly. (Discharge the air
												  trapped in EDL pneumatics by setting  the isolation vale to VENT)
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">Closing of Shut off Valve.</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  <h6>2</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td colspan="4">
												  <h6>Launcher Safe Mode</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">2.1</td>
											  <td>
												  On Barrel rotate the 5 way switch to SAFE position from its current
												  position.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">All the functions of Launcher will be inhibited.</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  <h6>3</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td colspan="4">
												  <h6>Launcher Vent Mode</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">3.1</td>
											  <td>
												  On Barrel rotate the 5-way switch to VENT position from its current
												  position.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">The air from the reservoir will get vented </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  <h6>4</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td colspan="4">
												  <h6>Launcher Controlled from RCU (ARM)</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.1</td>
											  <td>
												  Ensure that the PORT &amp; STBD launcher barrels are loaded with
												  an EAD as required
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">EAD present at required location.</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.2</td>
											  <td>
												  Ensure that the PORT &amp; STBD Launcher reservoir required have
												  been pressurized.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">90 bar pressure in the pressurised barrels </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.3</td>
											  <td>Switch the STBD &amp; PORT launcher i.e. LCU  ON</td>
											  <td valign="top">Supply Available power indicator glows</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.4</td>
											  <td>
												  Switch the ARM / SAFE / VENT / CHARGE valve for the PORT &amp;
												  STBD launcher barrels required to the ARM position
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">5-way valve to be positioned on ARM position</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.5</td>
											  <td>
												  Set the PORT &amp; STBD LAUNCHER SAFE / ENABLE KEY SWITCH on the
												  LCU to ENABLE and remove the Key.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  SAFE ENABLE key switch on Enable position and absence
												  of Key.
											  </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.6</td>
											  <td>
												  Set PORT &amp; STBD Launcher REMOTE / SAFE / LOCAL ARM to REMOTE
												  and remove the key.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM set to REMOTE position and
												  absence of key
											  </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.7</td>
											  <td>Turn the Power ON/OFF switch on the RCU to the ON position.</td>
											  <td valign="top">Supply Available power indicator glows</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.8</td>
											  <td>Insert a key into the RCU REMOTEARM / SAFE / AUTO ARM  key switch</td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  Availability of Key switch on RCU on AUTO/MANUAL
												  switch.
											  </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.9</td>
											  <td>
												  Turn and hold the key in the REMOTE ARM position. Sound alert
												  will be generated by both Launchers and will continue to be sound
												  whilst the key is held in the ARM position.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  Key positioned to REMOTE ARM position and sound is
												  audible and ready indicator glows.
											  </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.10</td>
											  <td>Depress the FIRE BUTTON on the selected barrel.</td>
											  <td>Release of Barrel, air through the selected reservoir.</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.11</td>
											  <td>
												  Release the REMOTE ARM / SAFE / AUTO ARM key and verify that it
												  returns to the SAFE position. The sound alarm on both the Launchers
												  will stop.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  REMOTE ARM / SAFE / AUTO ARM  key positioned to SAFE
												  position and no sound audible.
											  </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.12</td>
											  <td>Standby for the next launch or remove the ARM/SAFE key</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>5</td>
											  <td colspan="4">
												  <h6>Launcher Controlled from LCU (ARM)</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">5.1</td>
											  <td>
												  Ensure that the PORT &amp; STBD launcher barrels are loaded with
												  an EAD as required.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">EAD present at required location.</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">5.2</td>
											  <td>
												  Ensure that the PORT &amp; STBD launcher reservoirs required have
												  been pressurized.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">90 bar pressure in the pressurised barrels.</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">5.3</td>
											  <td valign="top">Switch the PORT &amp; STBD Launchers ON</td>
											  <td>Supply Available power indicator glows.</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">5.4</td>
											  <td>
												  Switch the ARM / SAFE / VENT / CHARGE valve for the PORT &amp;
												  STBD Launcher barrels required to the ARM position.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">5-way valve to be positioned on ARM position.</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">5.5</td>
											  <td>
												  Set the PORT &amp; STBD LAUNCHER SAFE / ENABLE key switch on the
												  LCU to ENABLE and remove the key.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  SAFE / ENABLE key switch positioned to ENABLE position
												  and absence of Key.
											  </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">5.6</td>
											  <td>
												  On LCU turn and hold the REMOTE/SAFE/LOCAL ARM key switch to LOCAL
												  ARM .An audible alert will be generated at the Launcher and will continue
												  to sound whilst the key is held in the ARM position.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  Key positioned to ARM position and sound is audible,
												  Ready Indicator glows.
											  </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">5.7</td>
											  <td valign="top">Depress the Fire Button for the selected barrel</td>
											  <td>Release of Barrel, air through the selected reservoir.</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">5.8</td>
											  <td>
												  Release the REMOTE / LOCAL ARM / SAFE key and verify that it returns
												  to the SAFE position. The audible alarm will stop
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  REMOTE / LOCAL ARM / SAFE key positioned to SAFE
												  position and no sound audible
											  </td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">5.9</td>
											  <td valign="top">Remove the REMOTE / LOCAL ARM / SAFE key</td>
											  <td>Absence of key on REMOTE / LOCAL ARM/SAFE switch</td>
											  <td></td>
											  <td></td>
										  </tr>
									  </tbody>
								  </table>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
					  <section id="2.7.4.2 Winch" level="5">
						  <title>2.7.4.2 Winch</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>
								  (<a
								onclick="javascript:parent.showPDF(&quot;../Author/Contents/NTDS/The_New_Torpedo_Defence_System/Technical_Manual/Images/Plate_3_10.pdf&quot;);parent.masterframe.rows=&quot;70%,30%&quot;"
								actuate="user">Wiring Diagram</a>)
							  </para>
							  <para>
								  <table frame="box" rules="all">
									  <colgroup>
										  <col width="13*"/>
										  <col width="43*"/>
										  <col width="42*"/>
									  </colgroup>
									  <tbody>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  <h6>Sl. No.</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <h6>Functional Description</h6>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <h6>Requirement</h6>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">1</td>
											  <td colspan="2">
												  The Winch utilizes 440V AC. All insulation and continuity
												  checks must be carried out before power cables are connected. Ensure
												  that all units of the Winch is properly connected and suitably grounded
												  before applying main power supply to the Winch.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">2</td>
											  <td valign="top">Switch ON the ship supply of the winch.</td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator  ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator ON</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local and Remote indicator OFF </li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
														  <li>Green Indicator at Proximity Sensors ON.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">3</td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  Release the ‘Emergency Stop’ Switch and press ‘Emergency
												  Reset’ Switch. Set the Standby / Operation Switch at Standby Position.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator  ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local and Remote indicator OFF.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator displays previous stored value</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">3.1</td>
											  <td valign="top"> Press the ‘Lamp Test’ Switch</td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>All Indicators in ON position.</li>
														  <li>Render and remote Buzzer sounding</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth display indicates “8888”.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">3.2</td>
											  <td valign="top">Depress the ‘Lamp Test’ switch</td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>All Indicators in initial position.</li>
														  <li>Render and remote Buzzer not sounding.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth display shows initial value”.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">3.3</td>
											  <td valign="top">Press the ‘Zero Dimmer’ Switch </td>
											  <td>
												  All indicators and Length and Depth display is in OFF condition,
												  though the MCP is in standby mode.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">3.4</td>
											  <td valign="top">Depress the ‘Zero Dimmer’ Switch</td>
											  <td>
												  All indicators and Length and Depth display is in ON condition
												  and shows current status.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">3.5</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>Press and Depress the Brightness control single switch.</para
>
												  <para>Repeat the above procedure in 5 steps of depress </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  Brightness of Tow Scope display decreases in five step on reaching
												  lowest brightness step, display regains its maximum brightness to
												  further decrease in 5 steps.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">3.6</td>
											  <td valign="top">Set the Local / Remote Switch at Local Position</td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator  ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indictor OFF</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local and Remote indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td rowspan="2" valign="top">3.7</td>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Drum Joystick at Payout
												  direction.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">Drum not rotating. </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Drum Joystick at Haul in
												  Direction.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">Drum not rotating. </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td rowspan="2" valign="top">3.8</td>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Level wind Joystick at
												  STBD direction.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">No displacement at Level Wind Assembly. </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Level Wind Joystick at
												  port Direction.
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">No displacement at Level wind assembly.</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">3.9</td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  <para>
													  Set the Local / Remote Switch at Remote Position
													  and Remote Not Connected.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Set the Local / Remote Switch
													  at Remote Position and Remote is Connected.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Move Drum
													  Joystic and Wind Level Joystic for operation
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator  ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local and Remote indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous value</li>
														  <li>Drum not rotating by Joystick.</li>
														  <li>No displacement for Level Wind Assembly by joystick.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">3.10</td>
											  <td valign="top">Set the maintenance mode switch at maintenance   </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>System Ready Indicator blinking.</li>
														  <li>
															  Enables override of  Over release stop and Excess Tow recovery
															  Switch
														  </li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4</td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  <para>
													  Set the Standby / Operation Switch at Operation
													  Position.
												  </para>
												  <para>Set Local / Remote at Local.</para>
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator  ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local indicator ON</li>
														  <li>Remote indicator OFF.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.1</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>Press the ‘Emergency Stop’ Switch.</para>
												  <para>
													  Move Drum
													  Joystic and Wind Level Joystic for operation
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator  ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator ON</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local indicator ON.</li>
														  <li>Remote indicator OFF.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
														  <li>Drum not rotating by Joystick</li>
														  <li>No displacement for Level Wind Assembly by joystick</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.2</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  Release the Emergency Stop Switch and Press Emergency Reset
													  Switch
												  </para>
												  <para>Move Drum Joystic and Wind Level Joystic for operation</para
>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator  ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator ON</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local indicator ON.</li>
														  <li>Remote indicator OFF.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
														  <li>Drum rotates by Joystick</li>
														  <li>Displacement for Level Wind Assembly by joystick</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.3</td>
											  <td> Press the ‘Lamp Test’ Switch</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>All Indicators in ON position.</li>
														  <li>Render and remote Buzzer sounding.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth display indicates “8888”.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.4</td>
											  <td>Depress the ‘Lamp Test’ switch</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>All Indicators in initial position.</li>
														  <li>Render and remote Buzzer not sounding.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth display shows initial value”.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.5</td>
											  <td valign="top">Press the ‘Zero Dimmer’ Switch </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  All indicators and Length and Depth display is in
												  OFF condition, though the MCP is in standby mode.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.6</td>
											  <td valign="top">Depress the ‘Zero Dimmer’ Switch</td>
											  <td>
												  All indicators and Length and Depth display is in ON condition
												  and shows current status.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.7</td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  <para>
													  Press and Depress the Brightness control single
													  switch.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  <h6>Repeat the above procedure in 5 steps of depresses.</h6
>
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td valign="top">
												  Brightness of Tow Scope display decreases in five
												  step on reaching lowest brightness step, display regains its maximum
												  brightness to further decrease in 5 steps.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.8</td>
											  <td>Set the Local / Remote Switch at Local Position</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator  ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indictor ON</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local indicator ON </li>
														  <li>Remote indicator OFF.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous stored value.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td rowspan="2" valign="top">4.9</td>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Drum Joystick at Payout
												  direction.
											  </td>
											  <td rowspan="2">Drum rotating in both direction.</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Drum Joystick at Haul in
												  Direction.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td rowspan="2" valign="top">4.10</td>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Level wind Joystick at
												  STBD direction.
											  </td>
											  <td rowspan="2">Displacement of Level wind Assembly is achieved.</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>
												  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Level Wind Joystick at
												  port Direction.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.11</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Joystick at STBD
													  direction for Level Wind Assembly.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Travel Extreme Condition
													  of STBD direction.
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Displacement of Level wind Assembly is started.</li>
														  <li>
															  Green indicator on Proximity sensors at both end (STBD and PORT
															  side) is ON
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  Yellow indicator on Proximity sensors at both end (STBD and PORT
															  side) is OFF
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  Once it reaches inside operating area of Proximity Sensor (STBD
															  side) it will stop the displacement of Level Wind assembly towards
															  STBD direction. Displacement towards Port Side is Possible
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  After step (d), Proximity Sensor (STBD Side) Green indicator and
															  Yellow indicator are ON position.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  At Proximity Sensor (PORT Side) Green indicator ON and Yellow
															  indicator in OFF position.
														  </li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.12</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  Press the Dead man Switch and Move the Joystick at PORT
													  direction for Level Wind Assembly.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Travel Extreme Condition
													  of PORT direction.
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Displacement of Level wind Assembly is started.</li>
														  <li>
															  Green indicator on Proximity sensors at both end (STBD and PORT
															  side) is ON.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  Yellow indicator on Proximity sensors at both end (STBD and PORT
															  side) is OFF.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  Once it reaches inside operating area of Proximity Sensor (PORT
															  side) it will stop the displacement of Level Wind assembly towards
															  PORT direction. Displacement towards STBD Side is Possible.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  After step (d), Proximity Sensor (PORT Side) Green indicator and
															  Yellow indicator are ON position.
														  </li>
														  <li>
															  At Proximity Sensor (STBD Side) Green indicator ON and Yellow
															  indicator in OFF position.
														  </li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.13</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  Set the Local / Remote Switch at Remote Position and Remote
													  Not Connected.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Move Drum Joystic and Wind Level Joystic
													  for operation
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator  ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indictor ON</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local indicator ON.</li>
														  <li>Remote indicator Blinking.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous value.</li>
														  <li>Drum rotating by Local Joystick.</li>
														  <li>Displacement for Level Wind Assembly by Local joystick.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.14</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  Set the Local / Remote Switch at Remote Position and Remote
													  Connected.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Move Drum Joystic and Wind Level Joystic for
													  operation on  Local Control Panel.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Level Joystic for operation
													  on Remote Control Panel.
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Supply available indicator  ON</li>
														  <li>Emergency Stop indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>System Ready Indictor ON</li>
														  <li>Motor Over temperature indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Local Indicator OFF</li>
														  <li>Remote indicator ON.</li>
														  <li>Length and Depth indicator display previous value.</li>
														  <li>Drum rotating by Remote Joystick. And not by Local Panel Joystic.</li>
														  <li>
															  Displacement for Level Wind Assembly by Remote joystick and not
															  by a Local panel.
														  </li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.15</td>
											  <td valign="top">Deploy the TOW Length 908 meter.</td>
											  <td>
												  Over Release Stop Switch is activated, it will not allow further
												  Deployment beyond 908 mtr. Recovery only is possible.
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.16</td>
											  <td>
												  Deploy the Tow till the 75 meters or less than that remains on
												  drum
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>At Cabinet SW2, 3, 4 are in closed position.</li>
														  <li>At cabinet SW1 and SW5 are in Open position.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.17</td>
											  <td>
												  Deploy the Tow till the 305 meters or less than that remains on
												  drum
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>At Cabinet SW3 and SW4 are in closed position.</li>
														  <li>At cabinet SW1, 2  and SW5 are in Open.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.18</td>
											  <td>
												  Deploy the Tow till the 466 meters or less than that remains on
												  drum
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>At Cabinet SW4 is in closed position.</li>
														  <li>At cabinet SW1, 2, 3 and SW5 are in Open condition.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>4.19</td>
											  <td>Deploy the Tow 200 meters </td>
											  <td valign="top">At cabinet SW1, 2, 3, 4 and 5 are in Open.</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr valign="top">
											  <td>4.20</td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  Bring the  motor in stop condition and release the Motor
													  electric Brake by Rotating  Manual release (two) Allen Bolt at Brake
													  Assembly once at clockwise direction.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Try to Rotate drum
													  motor by Manual Handle
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Engage the Motor electric Brake
													  by Rotating  Manual release (two) Allen Bolt at Brake Assembly once
													  at anti-clockwise direction.
												  </para>
												  <para>
													  Try to Rotate drum motor
													  by Manual Handle
												  </para>
											  </td>
											  <td>
												  <para>
													  <ol type="a">
														  <li>Drum can rotate manually in both direction. </li>
														  <li>Drum Cannot Rotate in any direction.</li>
													  </ol>
												  </para>
											  </td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td rowspan="3" valign="top">4.21</td>
											  <td>Set the maintenance mode switch at maintenance </td>
											  <td>System Ready Indicator blinking.</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>Set the Standby/ Operation switch at standby</td>
											  <td>Over release stop and access recovery switch override.</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td>Set the Standby/ Operation switch at Operation</td>
											  <td>Above observation are same during standby and operation mode</td>
										  </tr>
										  <tr>
											  <td valign="top">4.22</td>
											  <td>Recovered the complete tow on Drum and Press Cable Reset Switch</td>
											  <td valign="top">Length and Depth display shows ‘0000’</td>
										  </tr>
									  </tbody>
								  </table>
							  </para>
						  </content>
					  </section>
					  <section id="2.7.4.3 Console" level="5">
						  <title>2.7.4.3 Console</title>
						  <content>
							  <para>The console should pass following performance specifications:</para
>
							  <para>
								  <ol type="a">
									  <li>
										  All the Power selector switches on each NTDS Console should be
										  in working condition.
									  </li>
									  <li>All DC fans should be in working condition.</li>
									  <li>
										  The NTDS Console system must pass the Power ON self-test done
										  by BIOS diagnostics.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  NTDS Console must boot with pre-loaded operating system and reach
										  the specified stage.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  All the communication channels i.e. FO, USB etc must be in working
										  condition.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  All the Audio speakers, Audio amplifier board, Volume control
										  pot and headphone jack are in working condition.
									  </li>
									  <li>
										  All other interfaces like Mouse Pointer Device, Keyboard, Headphone,
										  etc. are in working condition.
									  </li>
								  </ol>
							  </para>
							  <para>
