                      is glowing then problem could be in LCU circuitry.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>(b)	LCU CPU Card may be faulty.</td>
                    <td>Replace LCU CPU Card.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="3">2</td>
                    <td rowspan="3">
                      On LCU, ‘POWER AVAILABLE’ lamp indicator fails to
                      light when switch ON mains.
                    </td>
                    <td>(a)	Ships mains power supply may not be available.</td>
                    <td>Check ships mains and switch ON.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>(b)	Lamp may be faulty.</td>
                    <td>
                      Press Lamp test push button provided on LCU and check if lamp
                      indicator glowing. If not glowing, replace lamp indicator. If lamp
                      is glowing then problem could be in LCU circuitry.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>(c)	Fuse may be faulty.</td>
                    <td>Replace fuse.</td>
                  </tr>
