                    <td>
                      <h6>Remedial Action</h6>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="2">1</td>
                    <td rowspan="2">Missed fire</td>
                    <td>(a)	Insufficient pressure to keep piston in safe position.</td>
                    <td>Insert pressure switch to maintain the pressure at designed value.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>(b)	Leakage at piston O-rings</td>
                    <td>Service O-ring.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="4">2</td>
                    <td rowspan="4">Solenoid valves-FVA does not fire</td>
                    <td>(a)	24V DC power supply may not be available to the solenoid.</td>
                    <td>Check power supply availability at solenoid.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>(b)	PLD Card could be defective</td>
                    <td>Replace PLD Card.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>(c)	Malfunctioning of solenoid valve.</td>
                    <td>Replace solenoid valve </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>(d)	Failures due to dirt accumulation</td>
                    <td>Remove dirt.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="2">3</td>
                    <td rowspan="2">Electrical connections -FVA does not fire</td>
                    <td>(a)	Loose connections</td>
                    <td>Check for any loose connections and tighten, if needed.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>(b)	Water may be drained inside EDL.</td>
                    <td>Use seals to avoid water to enter in to the EDL.</td>
                  </tr>
