        <section id="1.5.5 Troubleshooting- Console" level="4">
          <title>1.5.5 Troubleshooting- Console</title>
          <content>
            <para>
              <table frame="box" rules="all">
                <colgroup>
                  <col/>
                  <col/>
                  <col/>
                  <col/>
                </colgroup>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td>
                      <h6>Sl. No.</h6>
                    </td>
                    <td>
                      <h6>Fault Indication</h6>
                    </td>
                    <td>
                      <h6>Fault Diagnosis / Probable Cause</h6>
                    </td>
                    <td>
                      <h6>Remedial Action</h6>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="6">1</td>
                    <td rowspan="6">System does not switch ON</td>
                    <td>a)	No power Supply</td>
                    <td>Check input voltage at the source.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>b)	Faulty power cable.</td>
                    <td>
                      Check the continuity of power cable with multi-meter. If no continuity
                      found in any of the pins then replace power cable.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="4">c)	Faulty power selector switch.</td>
                    <td>Put the power selector switch in 1-PH/ 3-PH position.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>
                      Check the voltage at 1-PH Power Supply Module Input and Output,
                      when power selector switch is set to 1-PH. If no voltage is observed
                      then replace 1-PH Power Supply Module.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>
                      Check the voltage at 3-PH Power Supply Module Input and Output,
                      when power selector switch is set to 3-PH. If no voltage is observed
                      then replace 3-PH Power Supply Module.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>
                      Check the voltage at DC EMI Filter output. If no voltage is observed
                      then replace Filter.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="5">2</td>
                    <td rowspan="5">No Display</td>
                    <td>a)	Power supply to the LCD Display may not be available.</td>
                    <td>Check the LCD Display Power supply.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>b)	Faulty/ Loose Interface Cable/Connectors.</td>
                    <td>Replace/ Tighten Interface Cable/ Connectors.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>c)	Memory modules loose or faulty.</td>
                    <td>
                      Press the memory module in the socket properly or replace memory
                      module.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>d)	Riser Card loose contact or Faulty.</td>
                    <td>
                      Press the Riser Card connector in the socket properly or replace
                      Riser Card.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>e)	Graphics Card loose contact or Faulty.</td>
                    <td>
                      Press the Graphics Card connector in the slot properly or replace
                      Riser Card.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="3">3</td>
                    <td rowspan="3">System does not boot-up</td>
                    <td rowspan="3">CPU BIOS setup changed.</td>
                    <td>Press DEL/ F2 key to enter to the BIOS setup.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Check the SSD detection. If SSD is not detected, check the connection.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Check the Boot Sequence. Check the Boot Option.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="2">4</td>
                    <td rowspan="2">System Boots, but reports Error.</td>
                    <td>a)	BIOS POST test detected error.</td>
                    <td>Interpret Error Code and Correct.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>b)	OS Crash</td>
                    <td>Windows Display Appears and Disappears. Reinstall the OS.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="3">5</td>
                    <td rowspan="3">Touch Interface</td>
                    <td>a)	No touch Interface</td>
                    <td>Check the Serial connection.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>b)	Faulty/ Loose Interface Cable/Connectors.</td>
                    <td>Replace/ Tighten Interface Cable/ Connectors.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>c)	Touch displacement.</td>
                    <td>
                      <para>a)	Check by finger operation.</para>
                      <para>b)	Do the calibration</para
  >
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="6">6</td>
                    <td rowspan="6">Communication Error</td>
                     
                    <td rowspan="3">a)	FO Converters</td>
                    <td>a)	Check the input power supply.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>b)	Check the Power supply LED Indicators P1, P2.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>c)	Replace FO Converter(s).</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>b)	Faulty SFP Modules</td>
                    <td>
                      <para>a)	Check the LED Indicators G1, G2.</para>
                      <para>
                        b)	Replace
                        SFP Module(s).
                      </para>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="2">c)	Network Error</td>
                    <td>
                      <para>a)	Check the IP address </para>
                      <para>b)	Set the IP Address.</para
  >
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>
                      <para>c)	Check the NO Network symbol.</para>
                      <para>
                        d)	Check the
                        connection from SBC to FO converters with SFP Modules.
                      </para>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td rowspan="6">7</td>
                    <td rowspan="6">Audio Problem</td>
                    <td>a)	No Drivers</td>
                    <td>Check the drivers and install if not installed. </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>b)	Faulty/ Loose Interface Cable/Connectors.</td>
                    <td>Replace / Tighten Interface Cable/ Connectors.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>c)	Faulty Audio amplifier Board</td>
                    <td>
                      Check the connection between SBC to Audio amplifier board. If
                      faulty, replace the Audio amplifier board.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>d)	Faulty Volume control Pot</td>
                    <td>
                      Check the connection between SBC to Volume control Pot. If faulty,
                      replace the Volume control Pot.
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>e)	Faulty Speakers</td>
                    <td>Check the connection. If no sound, replace the Speaker(s).</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>f)	Faulty / Loose Interface Cable/Connectors.</td>
                    <td>Replace/ Tighten Interface Cable/ Connectors.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>8</td>
                    <td>Keypad Error</td>
                    <td>Faulty Keypad cable.</td>
                    <td>Check the cable continuity. If faulty, replace the cable.</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </para>
          </content>
        </section>
